{"id": "5601", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5601", "title": "Wyand the Shadow", "text": "Wyand was a member of the &lt;a href=\"High%20Council%20of%20Zakarum\"&gt;High Council of Zakarum&lt;/a&gt; during the 13th century. Enthralled by &lt;a href=\"Mephisto\"&gt;Mephisto&lt;/a&gt;, he and his fellow council members corrupted the faith from the inside. For this, they were rewarded by Mephisto, who transformed them into &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s and gave them abilities far beyond mere &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;s.\nWyand and his fellow council members were slain by a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20II\"&gt;group of heroes&lt;/a&gt; when they fought their way into &lt;a href=\"Travincal\"&gt;Travincal&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nDiablo II.\nWyand Voidbringer is a &lt;a href=\"super%20unique\"&gt;super unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Council%20Member\"&gt;Council Member 2&lt;/a&gt; who guards &lt;a href=\"Mephisto\"&gt;Mephisto&lt;/a&gt;'s chamber in the &lt;a href=\"Durance%20of%20Hate\"&gt;Durance of Hate&lt;/a&gt; in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\". He can &lt;a href=\"heal\"&gt;heal&lt;/a&gt; himself and teleport away after taking heavy damage.\nBonuses:\nDevelopment.\nIn beta SuperUniques.txt Wyand has 3 minions.\nWyand Voidbringer has an unused bloody color palette due to Council Member monsters lack of palshift.dat file and randtransform.dat file error in D2Client.dll\nDiablo IV.\nWyand features in the fifth of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\", as part of the &lt;a href=\"Fell%20Council\"&gt;Fell Council&lt;/a&gt;. He has been renamed to Wyand the Shadow."}
{"id": "24782", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24782", "title": "Wyatt Cheng", "text": "Wyatt Cheng is a principal game designer at &lt;a href=\"Blizzard%20Entertainment\"&gt;Blizzard Entertainment&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nCheng holds a B.S. in electrical engineering from Simon Fraser University. In addition to computer games, his hobbies include board and card games, as well as playing the guitar and cooking.\nCheng joined &lt;a href=\"Blizzard%20North\"&gt;Blizzard North&lt;/a&gt; in 2003. He contributed to bosses in \"&lt;a href=\"World%20of%20Warcraft\"&gt;World of Warcraft&lt;/a&gt;\", such as the Twin Emperors, Patchwerk, and the Four Horsemen. He worked on \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\" from the earliest days of its development., serving as the senior game designer He worked on the design of the &lt;a href=\"Witch%20Doctor\"&gt;Witch Doctor&lt;/a&gt;. He later served as the technical game designer for \"\". Cheng is currently the lead game designer for \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". Reportedly, Cheng wanted a break from \"Diablo III\", which he had worked on for ten years."}
