{"id": "40838", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40838", "title": "Wyrm (Cut)", "text": "The Wyrm is an cut &lt;a href=\"Animals\"&gt;Animal&lt;/a&gt; type. It was planned to be in a Infestation Quest where Wyrms would burst from the floor of a villager house and &lt;a href=\"Pepin\"&gt;Pepin&lt;/a&gt; would ask you to cleanse the place. After that quest was scrapped they were changed into a proper monster type. But after that they were soon cut too. \nOnly one single frame was made of their graphics, and just one single &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;Unique&lt;/a&gt;. They use &lt;a href=\"Skeleton\"&gt;Skeleton&lt;/a&gt; AI and work perfectly when enabled and made to use another monster graphics.\nThey have unused sounds, their folder includes both melee sounds and \"special\" sounds, with the later files sounding like they spit a glob of goo, suggesting that they were meant as enemies that use both melee and ranged combat.\nOne variant shares it's name with &lt;a href=\"Devourer\"&gt;Devourer&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;, though it is just a simple name reuse as these Wyrms seem to be creatures made of slime instead of being insects like the &lt;a href=\"Sand%20Maggot\"&gt;Sand Maggots&lt;/a&gt; are."}
