{"id": "52025", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52025", "title": "Xekorendaag, Ice Leviathan", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt; and member of the &lt;a href=\"Stormspawn\"&gt;Stormspawn&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nOf all the legends of the &lt;a href=\"Cold%20Isles\"&gt;Cold Isles&lt;/a&gt;, few tales terrify the children of &lt;a href=\"Pelghain\"&gt;Pelghain&lt;/a&gt; more than the myth of Xekorendaag. The legend says &lt;a href=\"Mehrwen\"&gt;Mehrwen&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ksathra\"&gt;Ksathra&lt;/a&gt;\u2019s fury cursed the isles so long as their descendants remained on Pelghain. When the people began to brave the deluges and hurricanes, arrogantly building tall cities and monuments, a great serpent drove into their settlements, consuming families and carving the isles apart as it did. Reproached, the people moved their settlements away from the capital, and the serpent faded to memory. The myth ends with a warning of Xekorendaag\u2019s return, reminding the people that they must protect their land and keep their settlements humble or again face the freezing of the seas and the devouring of their children.\nIn-game.\nXekorendaag is a &lt;a href=\"Helliquary\"&gt;Helliquary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", introduced in the &lt;a href=\"Nightmare%20Manifest\"&gt;Nightmare Manifest&lt;/a&gt; update. Defeating Xekorendaag on Difficulty I alone or with a party unlocks II (Paragon Levels 400-500).\nXekorendaag has a frozen state that makes it invulnerable to damage. "}
