{"id": "50297", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50297", "title": "Xereph of the Ancients", "text": "Xereph of the Ancients was a &lt;a href=\"nephalem\"&gt;nephalem&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Seeker\"&gt;Blood Seeker&lt;/a&gt; in service to Lord &lt;a href=\"Zir\"&gt;Zir&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnore was in the &lt;a href=\"City%20of%20the%20Ancients\"&gt;City of the Ancients&lt;/a&gt; when they and &lt;a href=\"Onore\"&gt;Onore&lt;/a&gt; fought against . Both were killed.\nIn-game.\nXereph was a &lt;a href=\"Super%20Unique\"&gt;Super Unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt; found in the City of the Ancients in the \"&lt;a href=\"Season%20of%20Blood\"&gt;Season of Blood&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"A%20Serpent%20Cornered\"&gt;A Serpent Cornered&lt;/a&gt;.\""}
{"id": "27923", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27923", "title": "Xian", "text": "The Xian are the people of the island of &lt;a href=\"Xiansai\"&gt;Xiansai&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nDue to Xiansai's insular nature, Xian culture developed free from major foreign influence. Xian society is dominated by the constantly competing &lt;a href=\"Great%20Families\"&gt;Great Families&lt;/a&gt;, which each controls a portion of their kingdom's economy. Xiansai's mountain ranges are littered with arcane repositories and an untold number of magical artifacts, leading some to suggest that Xiansai's people have practiced &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt; for millennia. \nCulture.\nXian religion is polytheistic, featuring 59 gods, albeit without any distinct hierarchy. The kingdom's priesthood has never formalized this religion, and the religion, such as it is, has not dissuaded the Xian from practicing &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt;. Of all these gods, it is only &lt;a href=\"Zei\"&gt;Zei&lt;/a&gt;, the Trickster, who is loved by the Xian. The Xian celebrate many holidays that are dedictated to one making a fool of themselves. The &lt;a href=\"Festival%20of%20Zei\"&gt;Festival of Zei&lt;/a&gt; is one such example. &lt;a href=\"Tong-Shi%27s%20Renewal\"&gt;Tong-Shi's Renewal&lt;/a&gt; is a festival named after &lt;a href=\"Tong-Shi\"&gt;Tong-Shi&lt;/a&gt;, and appears to have spread beyond Xiansai.\nAt least some Xian are aware of the existence of the &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Burning Hells&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "3576", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3576", "title": "Xiansai", "text": "Xiansai (pronounced \"shyan-sai\"), otherwise known as the Great Isle, is an island in &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;'s northern hemisphere\u2014within the &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Sea\"&gt;Frozen Sea&lt;/a&gt; and north-west of &lt;a href=\"Scosglen\"&gt;Scosglen&lt;/a&gt;. It is the home of the &lt;a href=\"Xian\"&gt;Xian&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nXiansai is Sanctuary's northernmost nation. Its mountain ranges are littered with arcane repositories and an untold number of magical artifacts, leading some to suggest that Xiansai's people have practiced magic for millennia. The &lt;a href=\"town\"&gt;town&lt;/a&gt;s and villages of Xiansai are widespread; a strong &lt;a href=\"horse\"&gt;horse&lt;/a&gt; and stronger barding are vital to travelers in the island's most dangerous regions.\nArts practicioned in Xiansai include the legal making of poisons. The island has a rich fishing industry, and exports silks.\nHistory.\nThe time before Xiansai's unification is referred to as a time of legends. The &lt;a href=\"Mage\"&gt;Mage&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Woh\"&gt;Woh&lt;/a&gt; and his companions herald from this age. \nXiansai was ruled by kings in antiquity. Reference has been made to emperors within Xian history.\nThe island was united through unification wars, which bought the Xian's &lt;a href=\"Great%20Families\"&gt;Great Families&lt;/a&gt; lands and titles they would claim as their eternal birthright.\nXiansai distanced itself from the &lt;a href=\"Sin%20War%20%28Event%29\"&gt;Sin War&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mage%20Clan%20Wars\"&gt;Mage Clan Wars&lt;/a&gt;, and other notable conflicts that plagued Sanctuary. However, the island has seen its share of civil strife. Many of its internal wars originated from the political maneuverings of the Great Families. \nIn antiquity, Xiansai trade with the empire of &lt;a href=\"Pelghain\"&gt;Pelghain&lt;/a&gt;. \nDuring the late 10th/early 11th centuries, Xiansai was in a period of internal strife.\nAt least up to &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231285\"&gt;1285&lt;/a&gt;, Mages from the &lt;a href=\"Yshari%20Sanctum\"&gt;Yshari Sanctum&lt;/a&gt; visited Xiansai every few years in search of prodigies that they could train in their specific vocations. The Xian who returned to their homeland as full-fledged Mages were highly sought after by the Great Families to fill the ranks of their personal armies."}
