{"id": "41381", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41381", "title": "Zakarum Scripture", "text": "Zakarum Scripture is a pair of &lt;a href=\"tome\"&gt;tome&lt;/a&gt;s that can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Wortham%20Chapel\"&gt;Wortham Chapel&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". One tome is to the player's left, the other on the right, at the chapel's far end. In that order, they read as follows:\n\"Be not fearless. For those without fear are those who have nothing precious to hold onto. Challenge fear. Overcome it. But deny it at your peril.\"\n\"Within &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;our&lt;/a&gt; hearts exists an ember of &lt;a href=\"light\"&gt;light&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Zakarum\"&gt;Zakarum&lt;/a&gt; feeds it. Protects it. Through faith and obedience alone can one's inner light fight the darkness.\""}
{"id": "5643", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5643", "title": "Zakarum Shield", "text": "The Zakarum Shield is an &lt;a href=\"Elite%20Items\"&gt;elite&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Paladin%20Shields\"&gt;paladin shield&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nPaladin Shields will also receive an &lt;a href=\"Auto%20Mod%23Paladin%20Shields\"&gt;Auto Mod&lt;/a&gt; that can either increase all &lt;a href=\"Resistances\"&gt;Resistances&lt;/a&gt; or provide boosts to &lt;a href=\"Damage\"&gt;Damage&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Attack%20Rating\"&gt;Attack Rating&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "45315", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45315", "title": "Zakarum Sigil", "text": "s are in-game items in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". They are used to activate &lt;a href=\"Horadric%20Altar\"&gt;Horadric Altar&lt;/a&gt;s in &lt;a href=\"difficulty\"&gt;difficulties&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nThe most assured way to get one is by defeating &lt;a href=\"Lord%20Martanos\"&gt;Lord Martanos&lt;/a&gt;. Defeating &lt;a href=\"Ming%20Shan%20the%20Devoted\"&gt;Ming Shan the Devoted&lt;/a&gt; has a chance to drop a Zakarum Sigil.\nThey also appear as quest items in \"&lt;a href=\"Tomb%20of%20the%20Word\"&gt;Tomb of the Word&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal%20Side%20Quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "5313", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5313", "title": "Zakarum Zealot", "text": "The Zakarum Zealot is a &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt; encountered in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nThe Zealots are directed by their Priests and will bring their righteous wrath down upon any who they believe to be tainted by the touch of the Three.\nReligious fanatics in service of &lt;a href=\"Zakarum\"&gt;Zakarum&lt;/a&gt;, the Zealots existed to bring down the unfaithful. Directed by &lt;a href=\"Zakarum%20Priest\"&gt;Zakarum Priest&lt;/a&gt;s, the Zealots brought down their wrath upon any who they believed to be tainted by the touch of the &lt;a href=\"Prime%20Evils\"&gt;Prime Evils&lt;/a&gt;.\nMasters of the polearm, they attacked without question or quarter; these attacks were coordinated, or unimaginative. They often worked together to bring down larger or stronger foes, surrounding the opponent in order to flank them.\nIn-game.\nZakarum Zealots move fast and attack with large &lt;a href=\"Scythe%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;scythes&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"axes\"&gt;axes&lt;/a&gt;, often delivering sweeping blows. They are deadly in combination with their &lt;a href=\"Zakarum%20Priest\"&gt;priests&lt;/a&gt;, who can &lt;a href=\"heal\"&gt;heal&lt;/a&gt; them. They also have a common habit of running away when their health hits critical levels.\nAfter the &lt;a href=\"Compelling%20Orb\"&gt;Compelling Orb&lt;/a&gt; is shattered , all Zakarum Zealots are freed of the evil trance, and start running away from the player.\nDevelopment.\nZakarum Zealots have their look before corruption in the game files as their unused base color palette shows them with their true skin color."}
