{"id": "16336", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16336", "title": "Zann Esu", "text": ""}
{"id": "149", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=149", "title": "Zann Esu Clan", "text": "The Zann Esu Clan is one of the oldest of the &lt;a href=\"Mage%20Clans\"&gt;Mage Clans&lt;/a&gt;. It is female-dominated, and its members are referred to as &lt;a href=\"Sorceress\"&gt;Sorceress&lt;/a&gt;es.\nLore.\nA mysterious and enigmatic people from the East, the Zann Esu are renowned for their strictly female caterie of magicians. They are on a quest for the \"perfect\" &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt; in its purest form. They feel that the other disciplines of magic are haphazard, and have instead chosen to focus strictly upon &lt;a href=\"elemental%20magic\"&gt;elemental magic&lt;/a&gt;. They mold the base elements into whatever magical forms they need - threatening all other magic disciplines with obsolescence. In order to achieve perfection in these elemental transmutations, they choose only those daughters of Sanctuary with the highest level of attunement to the magical elements. The Sorceresses believe that it is through the search for perfection that they will attain ultimate purity and ascend to their destined role as the most powerful mages in Sanctuary.\nAthletic, affable, and self-assured, Sorceresses hardly seem like scholarly bibliophiles hidden away from civilization. Sorceresses possess many of the same skills as the male members of Mage Clans, but excel at the use of elemental magic. Like most &lt;a href=\"mages\"&gt;mages&lt;/a&gt;, they consider melee combat vulgar, and use magic almost exclusively to fight their enemies.\nHistory.\nThe female mage clan of Zann Esu is one of the oldest of the ancient clans, although little is actually known about them. They stem from the followers of &lt;a href=\"Esu\"&gt;Esu&lt;/a&gt;.\nOrigins.\nCenturies ago, the fourteen powerful covens of Esu &lt;a href=\"witch\"&gt;witch&lt;/a&gt;es convened for the first time in generations. What they discussed is not known, but the witches left behind their former lives and, as a group, disappeared into the &lt;a href=\"Kehjistan\"&gt;Eastern jungles&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe exact location of the original Zann Esu community is a mystery. Until recently, their only contact with the outside world occurred during recruitment missions. Once every seven years, the Zann Esu visit certain families across &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;. These families have only one thing in common - they each have a seven-year-old daughter. Always good-natured and polite, the Zann Esu visitors meet the girls, ask a few questions and then leave. A select few of the girls are visited a second time and offered apprenticeships. The families of those chosen enjoy good fortune for many years.\nRecent History.\nFor centuries they studied in secret, perfecting their art and biding their time until the &lt;a href=\"Darkening%20of%20Tristram\"&gt;Emergence of Evil&lt;/a&gt;. Then, it was decreed, they would face their greatest challenge, either proving the purity of their magic or fading from existence. With &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;'s awakening in &lt;a href=\"Tristram\"&gt;Tristram&lt;/a&gt;, the Zann Esu &lt;a href=\"oracle\"&gt;oracle&lt;/a&gt;s decreed that the time of the Emergence was at hand. The destruction of the &lt;a href=\"Prime%20Evils\"&gt;Prime Evils&lt;/a&gt; would be the great test of their clan. Accordingly, Sorceresses were seen throughout Sanctuary, doing battle with the minions of evil wherever they were found. &lt;a href=\"Isendra\"&gt;One of their number&lt;/a&gt; joined a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20II\"&gt;group of heroes&lt;/a&gt; that slew the Prime Evils.\nAfter this, along with the other four Mage Clans, the Zann Esu came together in the &lt;a href=\"Yshari%20Sanctum\"&gt;Yshari Sanctum&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "29801", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29801", "title": "Zanthek", "text": "Zanthek, Prisoner is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Oppressor\"&gt;Oppressor&lt;/a&gt; found in the &lt;a href=\"Pandemonium%20Fortress\"&gt;Pandemonium Fortress&lt;/a&gt; Level 1 in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". He can be seen imprisoned on a platform below the area for the &lt;a href=\"Judgment%20%28event%29\"&gt;Judgment&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"event%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;event&lt;/a&gt;, but &lt;a href=\"Judge%20Alzarius\"&gt;Judge Alzarius&lt;/a&gt; summons him to attack &lt;a href=\"the%20Nephalem\"&gt;the Nephalem&lt;/a&gt; in the event's second phase.\nIn combat, he has the &lt;a href=\"Molten\"&gt;Molten&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Mortar\"&gt;Mortar&lt;/a&gt; traits, and is assisted by numerous &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Vermin\"&gt;Shadow Vermin&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Subjugator\"&gt;Subjugator&lt;/a&gt;s."}
{"id": "30968", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30968", "title": "Zao'Kapazao", "text": "Zao'Kapazao, Vilebat Keeper is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Morlu%20Caster\"&gt;Morlu Caster&lt;/a&gt; that appears in the &lt;a href=\"Blessed%20Chancel\"&gt;Blessed Chancel&lt;/a&gt; in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". He serves as the \"boss\" for the &lt;a href=\"Hellbreeder%20Nest\"&gt;Hellbreeder Nest&lt;/a&gt; , summoning minions throughout the encounter, which ends with his death. He and the event were added in &lt;a href=\"Patch%202.2.0%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Patch 2.2.0&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn combat, he has the &lt;a href=\"Desecrator\"&gt;Desecrator&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mortar\"&gt;Mortar&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Jailer\"&gt;Jailer&lt;/a&gt; traits. Up to 4 times, usually after losing at least 25% of his maximum &lt;a href=\"Life\"&gt;Life&lt;/a&gt;, he becomes briefly invulnerable - visually, shielded by a green force field - and teleports to a different corners of the platform. When approached, he summons 3 &lt;a href=\"Corrupt%20Hellbreeder\"&gt;Corrupt Hellbreeder&lt;/a&gt;s around himself, then becomes vulnerable again. Killing Zao'Kapazao ends the event, although any living nests and their &lt;a href=\"Vilebat\"&gt;Vilebat&lt;/a&gt; spawn will remain."}
{"id": "54297", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54297", "title": "Zarbinzet", "text": "Zarbinzet is a &lt;a href=\"town\"&gt;town&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Hawezar\"&gt;Hawezar&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nZarbinzet is surrounded by walls, and despite the hazards of Hawezar, it is able to survive, in part due to the &lt;a href=\"Crusaders\"&gt;Crusaders&lt;/a&gt; that garrison the town. Its faith lies with the &lt;a href=\"Zakarum\"&gt;Zakarum&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nThe bulk of the Crusaders arrived in Zarbinzet sometime during the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Enmity\"&gt;Great Enmity&lt;/a&gt;, as they searched for the &lt;a href=\"Tomb%20of%20Akarat\"&gt;Tomb of Akarat&lt;/a&gt;. They spent decades searching for the tomb, but to no avail.\nBy &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231336\"&gt;1336&lt;/a&gt;, the Crusaders were in a state of despair. They had used to keep the townsfolk safe from the threats beyond its walls, but their numbers had been whittled down, and others deserted the Order. The townsfolk became scared and looked to leave, and refused to go beyond the town walls.\nIn-game.\nZarbinzet appears in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\". It is the de facto capital of the Hawezar zone."}
{"id": "45593", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45593", "title": "Zatham", "text": "Zatham is a mysterious &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt; that came to aid of &lt;a href=\"Stormpoint\"&gt;Stormpoint&lt;/a&gt; when it was invaded by the &lt;a href=\"Cult%20of%20Terror\"&gt;Cult of Terror&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nEarly Life and Exile.\nZatham is an &lt;a href=\"Inari\"&gt;Inari&lt;/a&gt;, and was once one of the &lt;a href=\"Sanctifier\"&gt;Sanctifier&lt;/a&gt;s of &lt;a href=\"Ancients%27%20Cradle\"&gt;Ancients' Cradle&lt;/a&gt;. \nOver the years, the Inari gradually seized power on the island. Zatham accused the Elders of punishing misdeeds unevenly between Inari and Lilin. Events came to a head when &lt;a href=\"Morwith\"&gt;Morwith&lt;/a&gt; \u2014 one of the Elders of the Lilin, stole the Pathstone and abandoned the island with other Lilin who shared her view. &lt;a href=\"Ymuthrus\"&gt;Ymuthrus&lt;/a&gt; became the island's new &lt;a href=\"Prevailing%20Wind\"&gt;Prevailing Wind&lt;/a&gt; and ordered that any Lilin who had ever advocated fleeing the Cradle was to be executed. His edict shocked his fellow Inari, but only Zatham spoke out against it. \nFor his 'crime', Ymuthrus insisted Zatham judged in the rite of &lt;a href=\"Purity%27s%20Penance\"&gt;Purity's Penance&lt;/a&gt;. It did not kill Zatham, but burned the eyes from his face. Ymuthrus then permitted him exile. \nThe Bride.\nAngered by this betrayal, Zatham sought a means to get his vengeance \u2014 to bring destruction upon his once home. It has been an accepted fact amongst the residents of the Cradle that outsiders would bring destruction, so Zatham sought one that would help him achieve his goal. He later crossed paths with the &lt;a href=\"Bride%20of%20Hell\"&gt;Bride of Hell&lt;/a&gt;, and they came to an agreement \u2014 the &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;shard&lt;/a&gt;, for the destruction of the Cradle.\nTerror's Tide.\nWhen the Cult of Terror was close to breaching the &lt;a href=\"Stormpoint%20Battlement\"&gt;Stormpoint Battlement&lt;/a&gt;, Zatham came to the defenders aid, killing half dozen cultists without breaking a sweat. After they let him in, he asked the &lt;a href=\"Commander%20Kenton\"&gt;commander&lt;/a&gt; for a way into the &lt;a href=\"Abandoned%20Prison\"&gt;Abandoned Prison&lt;/a&gt;. The commander refused, so Zatham began to plan a strategy to attack the cult and stop their advancement to the prison.\nLuckily, &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;another adventurer&lt;/a&gt; came to Stormpoint's rescue, also looking for a way into the prison. Grateful for the assistance, he told the Shard-seeker to stop the cultists from advancing through the sea while he would go after their aerial reinforcement. After that, he jumped through a portal to go after the &lt;a href=\"Howling%20Terror\"&gt;Howling Terror&lt;/a&gt; as it was flying by.\nZatham met the Shard-seeker again in the Warden's office just after a &lt;a href=\"Deepstrider%20Behemoth\"&gt;sea behemoth&lt;/a&gt; captured a &lt;a href=\"Fern\"&gt;little girl&lt;/a&gt; in its rampage over its &lt;a href=\"Woodruh\"&gt;master's&lt;/a&gt; death. They chased the monster back to &lt;a href=\"Deepstrider%20Lair\"&gt;its lair&lt;/a&gt;. The &lt;a href=\"Esmund\"&gt;girl's brother&lt;/a&gt; dived into the water to save her. Zatham told the Shard-seeker to distract the beast while he rescued the children. Unfortunately, the boy drowned before he could be saved.\nAfter rescuing them, they were attacked by cultists; which was a distraction for &lt;a href=\"Akinees\"&gt;their leader&lt;/a&gt; to steal the &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt; shard.\nDestruction's Wake.\nReturning Home.\nThe Shard-seeker and Zatham pursued the Cult of Terror to &lt;a href=\"Ancients%27%20Cradle\"&gt;Ancients' Cradle&lt;/a&gt;. Zatham revealed to his companion that the island was once his home. Upon entering the island, they bore witness to the affliction that had ravaged the island, twisting many of its people, fauna and flora.\nThey caught up to the Bride of Hell as she attempted to sync her shard to the &lt;a href=\"Fire%20of%20Life\"&gt;Fire of Life&lt;/a&gt; using one of the obelisks scattered around the island. Luckily, the Fire rejected her and killed the cultists accompanying her in the backlash. As they confronted the Bride, she taunted them and teleported away. When Zatham tried to inspect the obelisk, he was also rebuffed, and the Fire of Life reanimated and fused the &lt;a href=\"corpse\"&gt;corpse&lt;/a&gt;s of the Cultists into &lt;a href=\"Limb%20Sower\"&gt;a monstrosity&lt;/a&gt; in retaliation. \nAfter defeating the monster, Zatham and his companion confronted &lt;a href=\"Rhyn\"&gt;Rhyn&lt;/a&gt; (a &lt;a href=\"Lilin\"&gt;Lilin&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Sanctifier\"&gt;Sanctifier&lt;/a&gt; that was captured by the Cultists). Zatham asked after his mother, as there were few more knowledgeable about the land than she. Rhyn didn't know where she was, but was able to cast a spell that would lead to her. Zatham asked his companion to find her.\nThe Shard-seeker returned with &lt;a href=\"Tarzoine\"&gt;Tarzoine&lt;/a&gt; (Rhyn's mother) and after a short exposition on the island, she directed them to the &lt;a href=\"Exiles%27%20Repose\"&gt;Elders'gathering place&lt;/a&gt; at the center of the island. Their journey went with little problems, apart from a brief confrontation with the Bride of Hell and having to protect themselves from the agitated defenses of the island they arrived at the Exiles' Repose.\nThe duo interrupted a meeting at the Exiles' Repose, and the Shard-seeker was bound by the Conservators. Zatham, unable to contain his fury, killed them and attacked Ymuthrus, but failed to kill him. Another elder called Geherit spoke for them.\nIn-game.\nZatham is an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". He was introduced in the quest \"&lt;a href=\"Unexpected%20Reinforcement\"&gt;Unexpected Reinforcement&lt;/a&gt;\", and accompanies the player for most of the quest line of \"&lt;a href=\"Terror%27s%20Tide\"&gt;Terror's Tide&lt;/a&gt;\", \"&lt;a href=\"Age%20of%20Falling%20Towers\"&gt;Age of Falling Towers&lt;/a&gt;\" and \"&lt;a href=\"Destruction%27s%20Wake\"&gt;Destruction's Wake&lt;/a&gt;\". After betraying the player, he's the second boss of the quest \"&lt;a href=\"Creation%27s%20Husk\"&gt;Creation's Husk&lt;/a&gt;\". He attacks with the following:\nPersonality and Traits.\nZatham was originally a very upright man who stood against evil, even when it is done by the law. His banishment from Ancients' Cradle left a mark on him, and led him to become obsessed in his pursuit of vengeance (which he saw as \"justice\" for the unjust acts done to him). \nHis vengeance didn't dim his desire to uphold justice and wipe out evil. Even after agreeing to work with the Bride he still killed terror cultists whenever he saw them harming innocents. He couldn't bring himself to kill &lt;a href=\"Geherit\"&gt;Geherit&lt;/a&gt;, who he saw as truly being a good person, and even planned to betray the &lt;a href=\"Cult%20of%20Terror\"&gt;Cult of Terror&lt;/a&gt; after their deal was completed."}
{"id": "36616", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=36616", "title": "Zatheria", "text": "Zatheria was a &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Hunter\"&gt;Demon Hunter&lt;/a&gt;. Alongside &lt;a href=\"Borax\"&gt;Borax&lt;/a&gt; the and &lt;a href=\"Patel\"&gt;Patel&lt;/a&gt; the &lt;a href=\"Wizard\"&gt;Wizard&lt;/a&gt;, she fought against a &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt; lord and his minions. They drew on their shared bond for strength to keep themselves from falling to their foes. In the end however, tired, cornered, and near death, they readied themselves for their final assault.\nTheir story was later recorded in \"&lt;a href=\"Chronicles%20of%20the%20North\"&gt;Chronicles of the North&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
