{"id": "3546", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3546", "title": "Battle Orders", "text": "Battle Orders is a &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"Although skillful in single combat, the Barbarian warrior also has a talent for group tactics. It is this ability that makes him a natural leader in combat. An experienced warrior can use this skill to better array his forces in battle, enhancing their ability to overcome the enemy. \"\nGeneral Information.\nSynergies.\nCasting Battle Orders greatly increases Life, Mana, and Stamina. If either Life or Mana are not full at the moment of skill being cast, it sets the current Life and Mana to same percentage as before skill activation.\nIt is an extremely popular skill used in parties, due to the fact that when maxed, it almost doubles anyone's Life and Mana. Multiple Battle Orders do not stack, so, it is best that the player with the most skill points in this skill cast it for the entire party. Moreover, overwriting it with lower level Battle Orders will decrease the current Life and Mana of players, and can lead to easy deaths of party members in dangerous situations.\nIn earlier builds, Battle Orders enhanced the affected players' maximum\u00a0Life and Mana only, leaving the orbs unfilled even if they were previously maxed out. In later versions of the game, both maximum and current reserves are increased.\nSkill Progression.\nMana Cost: 7\nRadius: 12.6 yards\n\"Note that the durations in the table may seem deceptive, as the synergy with its prerequisite increases its duration by at least 5 seconds.\""}
{"id": "43165", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43165", "title": "Battle Pass", "text": "The Battle Pass (a.k.a. Season Pass) is a monetization feature of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\" and \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDiablo Immortal.\nBattle Pass rotates once every 4 weeks. There is a free track and a premium track (called Empowered Battle Pass).\nThe Battle Pass can be leveled up by collecting &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Points\"&gt;Battle Points&lt;/a&gt; from various activities.\nRewards.\nCorrect as of May 2024.\nThe total number of points to reach rank 40 is 6240, which can be achieved by earning an average of 222.86 points per day.\nDiablo IV.\nThe Season pass gives players greater rewards as they play more throughout the . It is divided between free tiers (unlocked just by playing the game and leveling), and premium tiers, which provide no in-game power or advantage over other players. The free tiers of the pass will provide gameplay boosts to all players\u2014things which make the journey of leveling up a fresh seasonal character faster and more streamlined. In contrast, the premium tier rewards are focused on aesthetics, providing a huge value in the form of cosmetics and premium currency. A third tier, accelerated, can be purchased, which allows players to skip 20 levels of the premium pass.\nMany of the rewards embody the seasonal theme, helping players show off their participation in that Season. At any point during the Season, players can purchase the premium pass to unlock the ability to earn premium rewards tiers containing seasonally themed cosmetics and premium currency. The Season Pass is expected to cost $10 USD, while the accelerated pass costs $25 USD. Regardless of the case, each Battle Pass has 90 levels of rewards.\nThe Season Journey accelerates Season Pass progression. While any play style can progress through the Season Pass, min-maxers can focus on Season Journey objectives to advance more quickly. It is expected to take 75 hours of playtime to complete each Battle Pass.\nBattle Pass progression is shared between platforms."}
{"id": "53428", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53428", "title": "Battle Pass Season (Diablo Immortal)", "text": "&lt;a href=\"Battle%20Pass\"&gt;Battle Pass&lt;/a&gt; seasons are a feature in &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;. Each season lasts 4 weeks, and introduces a new cosmetic along with resetting &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Points\"&gt;Battle Points&lt;/a&gt; progress.\nBattle Pass seasons should not be confused with &lt;a href=\"List%20of%20Diablo%20Immortal%20game%20updates\"&gt;game update&lt;/a&gt; content, although they are announced in the same posts on Blizzard's Diablo Immortal news page.\nSeason 2.\nSeason 2 was themed around the &lt;a href=\"Bloodsworn\"&gt;Bloodsworn&lt;/a&gt;. It released on July 7, 2022, and ran until August 4, 2022. It included the following:\nSeason 3.\nSeason 3 began on August 4, and ended on September 1. It included the following:\nSeason 4.\nSeason 4 began on September 1, and ran until September 29. It introduced the following:\nSeason 5.\nSeason 5 began on September 21, and ran until October 27. It introduced the &lt;a href=\"Forgotten%20Nightmares\"&gt;Forgotten Nightmares&lt;/a&gt; major update.\nSeason 6.\nSeason 6 began on October 27, and ran until November 24. It introduced the &lt;a href=\"Below%20the%20Sands\"&gt;Below the Sands&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"cosmetic%20set\"&gt;cosmetic set&lt;/a&gt; and battle pass.\nSeason 7.\nSeason 7 ran from November 24 to December 22, 2022. It introduced the following:\nSeason 8.\nSeason 8 began on December 22, at 3:00 a.m. server time, and ran until January 19, at 2:59 a.m. server time. It included the &lt;a href=\"Terror%27s%20Tide\"&gt;Terror's Tide&lt;/a&gt; update, and the &lt;a href=\"Hidden%20Sun\"&gt;Hidden Sun&lt;/a&gt; cosmetic set.\nSeason 9.\nSeason 9 began on January 19, at 3:00 a.m. server time, and will run until February 16, 2:59 a.m. server time. It includes the &lt;a href=\"Wicked%20Wanderer\"&gt;Wicked Wanderer&lt;/a&gt; cosmetic set.\nSeason 10.\nSeason 10 began February 16, at 3:00 a.m. server time. It ran until March 16, at 2:59 a.m. server time. It included the &lt;a href=\"Alchemist%27s%20Admixture\"&gt;Alchemist's Admixture&lt;/a&gt; cosmetic set.\nSeason 11.\nSeason 11 began March 13, at 2:59 a.m. server time. It includes the &lt;a href=\"Sea%20Reavers\"&gt;Sea Reavers&lt;/a&gt; cosmetic set.\nSeason 13.\nSeason 13 began May 11, 2023, and ended on June 8, 2:59 a.m server time. It includes the &lt;a href=\"Knights%20Penitent%20%28Cosmetic%20Set%29\"&gt;Knights Penitent&lt;/a&gt; cosmetic set.\nSeason 14.\nSeason 14 began June 8, 2023, and ended on June 29. It included the &lt;a href=\"Children%20of%20Lilith\"&gt;Children of Lilith&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hatred%27s%20Heritage\"&gt;Hatred's Heritage&lt;/a&gt; cosmetic sets.\nSeason 15.\nSeason 15 began July 6, 2023, and ran until August 3. It included the &lt;a href=\"Bronze%20Wardens\"&gt;Bronze Wardens&lt;/a&gt; cosmetic set.\nSeason 16.\nSeason 16 began on August 3, 2023, and ran until August 31. It introduced the &lt;a href=\"Howling%20Terror%20%28Cosmetic%20Set%29\"&gt;Howling Terror&lt;/a&gt; cosmetic set.\nSeason 17.\nSeason 17 ran from August 31 to September 28, 2023. It introduced the &lt;a href=\"Ruptured%20Soul\"&gt;Ruptured Soul&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"Walking%20Nightmare\"&gt;Walking Nightmare&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"cosmetic%20set\"&gt;cosmetic set&lt;/a&gt;s.\nSeason 18.\nSeason 18 ran from September 28 to October 26, 2023. It featured the &lt;a href=\"Fresh%20Meat\"&gt;Fresh Meat&lt;/a&gt; cosmetic set and &lt;a href=\"Deathless%20Destiny\"&gt;Deathless Destiny&lt;/a&gt; Phantom Market.\nSeason 19.\nSeason 19 ran from October 26 to November 23, 2023. It featured the &lt;a href=\"Spawn%20of%20Destruction\"&gt;Spawn of Destruction&lt;/a&gt; cosmetic. \nSeason 20.\nSeason 20 ran from November 23 to December 21, 2023. It introduced the &lt;a href=\"Unholy%20Passengers\"&gt;Unholy Passengers&lt;/a&gt; cosmetic\nSeason 22.\nSeason 22 began on January 18, 2024. It introduced the &lt;a href=\"Plague%20Reaper\"&gt;Plague Reaper&lt;/a&gt; cosmetic.\nSeason 23.\nSeason 23 ran from February 15 - March 14, 2024. It included the following:\nSeason 24.\nSeason 24 ran from March 14 to April 11, 2024. It included the following:\nSeason 25.\nSeason 25 ran from April 11 to May 9, 2024. It included the following:\nSeason 26.\nSeason 26 ran from May 9 to June 6, 2024. It included the following:\nSeason 27.\nSeason 27 ran from June 6 to July 4, 2024. It included the following:\nSeason 28.\nSeason 28 ran from from July 4 to August 1, 2024. It included the following:\nSeason 29.\nSeason 29 ran from August 1 to August 29, 2024. It included the following:\nSeason 30.\nSeason 30 ran from August 29 to September 26, 2024. It included the following:\nSeason 31.\nSeason 31 runs from September 26 to October 24, 2024. It includes the following:\nSeason 32.\nSeason 32 ran from October 24 to November 21, 2024. It included the following:"}
