{"id": "142", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=142", "title": "Bear Tribe", "text": "The Bear Tribe is a tribe. \nLore.\nThe Bear Tribe are the wisest of the Barbarian tribes, and are known to have produced various poultices. Those that hail from the tribe are masters of the &lt;a href=\"maces\"&gt;mace&lt;/a&gt;, and advocate a close grappling form of combat.\nAmong the Bear Tribe, one who is no longer useful can depart safely in exile, bringing sturdy clothing and armor, but leaving behind their weapons, food, spouses and children.\nThe Bear Tribe worships a &lt;a href=\"deity\"&gt;deity&lt;/a&gt; called &lt;a href=\"Ursus\"&gt;Ursus&lt;/a&gt;. \nHistory.\nThe Bear and &lt;a href=\"Crane%20Tribe\"&gt;Crane Tribe&lt;/a&gt;s were wary of each other for many generations. At a point, they broke &lt;a href=\"Stonefall\"&gt;a hammer&lt;/a&gt; to buy peace with the Crane. The hammer was reforged by both together to crash upon a shared foe.\nThe Bear Tribe was among those who fought against &lt;a href=\"Rakkis\"&gt;Rakkis&lt;/a&gt; in his attempted conquest of the &lt;a href=\"Northern%20Steppes\"&gt;Northern Steppes&lt;/a&gt;. Rakkis and his forces were eventually beaten back, but at the cost of many lives, including the tribe's chief.\nNot long before the &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt;'s destruction, the Crane and Bear Tribes commingled and shared their powerful techniques with all who would learn. \nAfter the destruction of the Worldstone, a small number of Bear Tribe members departed the &lt;a href=\"Dreadlands\"&gt;Dreadlands&lt;/a&gt; to search for a new home. They established the &lt;a href=\"Bear%20Tribe%20Refuge\"&gt;Bear Tribe Refuge&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Fractured%20Peaks\"&gt;Fractured Peaks&lt;/a&gt;. However, some came to inhabit the &lt;a href=\"Dry%20Steppes\"&gt;Dry Steppes&lt;/a&gt; among the &lt;a href=\"Ox%20Tribe\"&gt;Ox&lt;/a&gt; and Crane tribes. They fought against the &lt;a href=\"Cannibals\"&gt;Cannibals&lt;/a&gt;."}
