{"id": "3175", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3175", "title": "Ber Rune", "text": "A Ber rune is a high &lt;a href=\"Runes\"&gt;rune&lt;/a&gt; which can be &lt;a href=\"socket\"&gt;socket&lt;/a&gt;ed into equipment in \"\". Ber is an extremely rare rune, and it is often considered the most valuable, due to its use in multiple popular &lt;a href=\"Rune%20Words\"&gt;rune words&lt;/a&gt;, and its &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20Blow\"&gt;crushing blow&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"damage%20reduction\"&gt;damage reduction&lt;/a&gt; mods.\nEffects.\nSocketing an item with a Ber rune increases the item's level requirement to 63, unless it was already higher.\nSources.\nThe Act 3 (H) Good treasure class has a chance to drop a Ber rune, as do higher Good treasure classes.\nIn single-player, open or ladder games only, the &lt;a href=\"Horadric%20Cube\"&gt;Horadric Cube&lt;/a&gt; can transmute two &lt;a href=\"Sur%20Rune\"&gt;Sur runes&lt;/a&gt; and one flawless amethyst into one Ber rune.\nRune Words.\nBer runes are used in these &lt;a href=\"Rune%20Words\"&gt;rune words&lt;/a&gt;:\nRecipes.\nBer runes are used in one &lt;a href=\"Horadric%20Cube\"&gt;Horadric Cube&lt;/a&gt; recipe."}
