{"id": "24229", "revid": "35062833", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24229", "title": "Berserker Rage", "text": "Berserker Rage\u00a0is a\u00a0\u00a0passive skill in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", unlocked at level 20.\nIn-game.\nThe bonus is determined by the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Fury\"&gt;Fury&lt;/a&gt; present\u00a0\"before\"\u00a0the attack occurs. Thus, an attack that starts above the threshold but causes Fury to fall below it will\u00a0receive the bonus, while an attack that starts below the threshold but generates enough Fury to end above the threshold will not receive the bonus."}
