s unevenly between Inari and Lilin, though it was the sacred responsibility of the &lt;a href=\"Conservator\"&gt;Conservator&lt;/a&gt;s and Elders to assign such punishments, and his as a Sanctifier to carry them out.\"\n\"Ymuthrus insisted he be judged in the rite of &lt;a href=\"Purity%27s%20Penance\"&gt;Purity's Penance&lt;/a&gt;. It did not kill Zatham, but burned the eyes from his face. Ymuthrus then permitted him exile. It was, by his standards, generous.\""}
