{"id": "27701", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27701", "title": "Bile Crawler", "text": "Bile Crawlers\u00a0are demonic enemies in the of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". They are the more powerful variant of &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Vermin\"&gt;Shadow Vermin&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nBile Crawlers usually hide within the growths of demonic corruption in the &lt;a href=\"High%20Heavens\"&gt;High Heavens&lt;/a&gt;, pouring forth from it when the cluster is destroyed. They appear one by one (so it's hard to hit them all at once), 8-10 per cluster. Some are also found in &lt;a href=\"Hell%20Rift\"&gt;Hell Rift&lt;/a&gt;s. They are significantly stronger and just as fast, but less numerous than Shadow Vermin.\nOnce the players bypass the &lt;a href=\"Gardens%20of%20Hope\"&gt;Gardens of Hope&lt;/a&gt;, the Bile Crawlers are no longer encountered.\nIn , Bile Crawlers are replaced with similar, but &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skeletal%20Crawler\"&gt;Skeletal Crawler&lt;/a&gt;s."}
{"id": "37466", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37466", "title": "Bilefen", "text": "Bilefen Island, more commonly just called Bilefen, or \"the Bilefen\", is a jungle island located just south of &lt;a href=\"Aranoch\"&gt;Aranoch&lt;/a&gt;. It is frequented by pirates and traders alike, though none extend their stay.\nLore.\nMurky waterways run across the island, and the island is dotted by ancient abandoned temples. Altruism is rare on this island.\nHistory.\nIn ages past, Bilefen was inhabited by the &lt;a href=\"nephalem\"&gt;nephalem&lt;/a&gt; as part of the kingdom of &lt;a href=\"Valostre\"&gt;Valostre&lt;/a&gt;. Due to the actions of &lt;a href=\"Sargoth\"&gt;Sargoth&lt;/a&gt;, Valostre fell into ruin.\nAt some point, &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;s arrived on &lt;a href=\"Bilefen\"&gt;Bilefen&lt;/a&gt;. Later, &lt;a href=\"Westmarch\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt; established a number of settlements This was apparently long after the initial human settlement.\nWhen the &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt; was destroyed, one of its fragments landed here, making a bad situation worse for those who lived on the island. \nBy &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Green%20Death\"&gt;plague&lt;/a&gt; was spreading across the island, with &lt;a href=\"Plague%20Carrier\"&gt;Plague Carrier&lt;/a&gt;s serving as the apparent vectors. Human and beast alike succumbed to it, and when the infection had run its course, the victim was left an empty husk.\nAlso by this year, the island's &lt;a href=\"Fetish\"&gt;Fetish&lt;/a&gt; were attacking the island's settlements, including Port Justinian itself. Demonic destruction flooded the island's waterways, grinding daily life to a sludgy halt.\nIn-game.\nThe island appears as a zone in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It has a recommended &lt;a href=\"Character%20Level\"&gt;Character Level&lt;/a&gt; of 40-45.\nPlaying through the storyline of \"Immortal\", players will reach it from the &lt;a href=\"Library%20of%20Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;Library of Zoltun Kulle&lt;/a&gt;. A &lt;a href=\"terminus\"&gt;terminus&lt;/a&gt; will deposit them on the eastern side of the island. Alternatively, they can use &lt;a href=\"Captain%20Rehm\"&gt;Captain Rehm&lt;/a&gt;, who will deposit them on the western side of the island, close to &lt;a href=\"Port%20Justinian\"&gt;Port Justinian&lt;/a&gt;."}
