{"id": "25494", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=25494", "title": "Bind on Account", "text": "Bind on Account, or BoA for short, is a way of describing an item that cannot be traded to other players. The item can still be transferred among characters on the same account. This is implemented in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAll &lt;a href=\"Gold\"&gt;gold&lt;/a&gt; is account bound, as are all crafting materials (except &lt;a href=\"Exquisite%20Essence\"&gt;Exquisite Essence&lt;/a&gt;,\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Iridescent%20Tear\"&gt;Iridescent Tear&lt;/a&gt;, and\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Fiery%20Brimstone\"&gt;Fiery Brimstone&lt;/a&gt;) , quest items, and\u00a0marquise and higher\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Gems\"&gt;gems&lt;/a&gt;. Gems below marquise can still be traded.\nAll &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;legendary&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Set%20Items\"&gt;set&lt;/a&gt; items dropped since patch 2.0 are account bound, to an extent. The item will be tradeable for the next two hours of gameplay to any player that was in the same game when the item was dropped. After two hours of gameplay, the item will be permanently bound to the account in possession of it. Crafted legendary and set items are account bound as soon as they are crafted, regardless of the presence of other players.\nItems of any quality weaker than Legendary/Set items will only become Account-Bound if they are &lt;a href=\"Enchanting\"&gt;enchanted&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"socket\"&gt;socket&lt;/a&gt;ed with Account-Bound gems or otherwise modified."}
{"id": "54372", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54372", "title": "Binding Bronze of Shal'baas", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"bracelet\"&gt;bracelet&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;,\" and part of the \"&lt;a href=\"War%20Rags%20of%20Shal%27baas\"&gt;War Rags of Shal'baas&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"item%20set\"&gt;item set&lt;/a&gt;. \nStats.\n "}
{"id": "33402", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=33402", "title": "Binding Evil", "text": "Binding Evil is a minor that may occur in &lt;a href=\"Act%20V%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act V&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It takes place on &lt;a href=\"Greyhollow%20Island\"&gt;Greyhollow Island&lt;/a&gt;, which only appears in &lt;a href=\"Adventure%20Mode\"&gt;Adventure Mode&lt;/a&gt;. Either &lt;a href=\"Ghost%20Prison\"&gt;Ghost Prison&lt;/a&gt; or Binding Evil will always appear in every game.\nThe Nephalem may find &lt;a href=\"The%20Crazed%20Man\"&gt;The Crazed Man&lt;/a&gt; sacrificing a human on an altar. Talking to him prompts him to attack, hitting very hard immediately. Upon his death, two &lt;a href=\"Wildwood%20Bulwark\"&gt;Primal Wildwoods&lt;/a&gt; to the left and right of the altar will awaken. They are much more powerful than normal Bulwarks, and have the green gas cloud sprout attack like &lt;a href=\"Wood%20Wraith\"&gt;Wood Wraith&lt;/a&gt;s. Primal Splinter remnants emerge when they are killed, and must be defeated as well. \nThe event ends when all the plants are dead, awarding &lt;a href=\"gold\"&gt;gold&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"experience\"&gt;experience&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Crazed Man drops \"&lt;a href=\"Testament%20of%20My%20Failure\"&gt;Testament of My Failure&lt;/a&gt;\", one part at a time in succession, if the player has not already obtained them all.\nDialogue.\nThe Crazed Man's prayer is Latin, and translates to \"You are blessed goddess Nereza is the greatest. Our worthy grace and love!\""}
