{"id": "44821", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44821", "title": "Black Mists", "text": "The is a phenomenon that has covered &lt;a href=\"Misty%20Valley\"&gt;parts&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Zavain\"&gt;Mount Zavain&lt;/a&gt; since the time of the &lt;a href=\"Zakarum%20Crusade\"&gt;Zakarum Crusade&lt;/a&gt;. It's existence is heavily related to the &lt;a href=\"Ancient%20Nightmare\"&gt;Ancient Nightmare&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe mists are &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;ic in nature, and can be repelled with the presence of the &lt;a href=\"Light\"&gt;Light&lt;/a&gt;. The is toxic to the living; draining their essence. In high concentration (around the Ancient Nightmare), it can be fatal. directly produced by the Ancient Nightmare contains such potent hatred that it sloughs flesh from bone.\nPeople who die within concentrated turn into &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Nightmare%20%28demon%29\"&gt;nightmares&lt;/a&gt; usually gestate within their bodies. Corpses directly infested by the turn into &lt;a href=\"Pustuant%20Hulk\"&gt;hideous monsters&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "10095", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10095", "title": "Black Mushroom", "text": "The Black Mushroom is an item used to craft the , which can be used to gain access to &lt;a href=\"Whimsyshire\"&gt;Whimsyshire&lt;/a&gt; and is required to complete the &lt;a href=\"Altar%20of%20Rites\"&gt;Altar of Rites&lt;/a&gt;. It has a chance to be found in the &lt;a href=\"Tristram%20Cathedral\"&gt;Cathedral&lt;/a&gt; Level 1 in any game mode or difficulty.\nThe mushroom is rare and players may need to create new game sessions multiple times before finding it. Each time will generate a new map with the possibility of containing the mushroom, but of course with a fresh batch of enemies to wade through.\nThe item is looted from a patch of lightly glowing violet mushrooms. When clicked, this container makes a sound like an opening chest, and a male voice may be heard uttering \"whoa\". After picking it up, &lt;a href=\"The%20Nephalem\"&gt;The Nephalem&lt;/a&gt; comments on the impressive size of the mushrooms, a\u00a0homage to the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Mushroom%20%28Quest%29\"&gt;Black Mushroom quest&lt;/a&gt; in the original \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28game%29\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "111", "revid": "192145", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=111", "title": "Black Mushroom (Quest)", "text": "\"For the Diablo III item Black Mushroom, see &lt;a href=\"Black%20Mushroom\"&gt;Black Mushroom&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nThis cave quest involves running some errands for &lt;a href=\"Adria\"&gt;Adria&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Pepin\"&gt;Pepin&lt;/a&gt;. It is initiated by presenting the &lt;a href=\"Fungal%20Tome\"&gt;Fungal Tome&lt;/a&gt;, an item found on the &lt;a href=\"Level%209%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;ninth level&lt;/a&gt; of the labyrinth, to Adria the Witch. She will tell the hero to find a &lt;a href=\"Black%20Mushroom\"&gt;Black Mushroom&lt;/a&gt;. Also on the ninth floor is a patch of mushrooms. Clicking on the mushroom patch (but only after delivering the Fungal Tome to Adria) will drop the Black Mushroom which can then be conveyed to Adria.\nAdria will inform the hero that Pepin wants the brain of a demon for an elixir, which she then wants for herself. The next monster killed anywhere, be it the Cathedral, or Hell itself, will yield the necessary brain. When Pepin is given the brain, he rewards the hero with the &lt;a href=\"Spectral%20Elixir\"&gt;Spectral Elixir&lt;/a&gt;. By now, Adria has completed her recipe and does not need the elixir, so she will tell the hero to keep it. Thus, the Spectral Elixir, which boosts each of the four primary stats by +3, becomes the reward for the quest.\nNPC Dialogue.\nInitiation:\n&lt;a href=\"Deckard%20Cain\"&gt;Deckard Cain&lt;/a&gt;:\n&lt;a href=\"Griswold\"&gt;Griswold&lt;/a&gt;:\n&lt;a href=\"Gillian\"&gt;Gillian&lt;/a&gt;:\n&lt;a href=\"Farnham\"&gt;Farnham&lt;/a&gt;:\n&lt;a href=\"Ogden\"&gt;Ogden&lt;/a&gt;:\n&lt;a href=\"Wirt\"&gt;Wirt&lt;/a&gt;:\n&lt;a href=\"Adria\"&gt;Adria&lt;/a&gt;, First Return:\n&lt;a href=\"Adria\"&gt;Adria&lt;/a&gt;, Second Return:\n&lt;a href=\"Pepin\"&gt;Pepin&lt;/a&gt;, First Return:\n&lt;a href=\"Adria\"&gt;Adria&lt;/a&gt;, Returning with brain:\n&lt;a href=\"Pepin\"&gt;Pepin&lt;/a&gt;, Second Return:\nCharacter:\nCompletion:\nDiablo III.\nThis quest does not reappear per se in &lt;a href=\"The%20Darkening%20of%20Tristram\"&gt;The Darkening of Tristram&lt;/a&gt; event in &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;, but finding the &lt;a href=\"Rotten%20Mushroom\"&gt;Rotten Mushroom&lt;/a&gt; will lead to a similar chain of events, ultimately rewarding player with and &lt;a href=\"Royal%20Calf\"&gt;Royal Calf&lt;/a&gt;."}
