{"id": "51745", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51745", "title": "Black weapon", "text": "\"Black weapon\" is a slang term for a &lt;a href=\"weapon\"&gt;weapon&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\" with added &lt;a href=\"Physical\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; damage as a magic property rather than any other type of &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20Damage\"&gt;Elemental Damage&lt;/a&gt;. Prior to \"\", these weapons received a larger benefit from percentage bonuses to weapon damage due to a long-standing bug in damage calculation: those bonuses applied to any Physical damage from the weapon, which for black weapons included all damage, but for others only included base damage without the added elemental damage. Their total damage potential was higher than other weapons as a result, and were often valued more than other weapons by players.\nThe term \"black weapon\" originates from the in-game tooltip for &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Items\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Rare%20Items\"&gt;Rare&lt;/a&gt; weapons, which has a colorful design in the background matching its added elemental damage type. Added Physical damage has no such design, leaving the tooltip black."}
{"id": "9354", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9354", "title": "Blackash the Burning", "text": "Blackash the Burning is a &lt;a href=\"Unique_Monsters\"&gt;Unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20Archer\"&gt;Burning Dead Archer&lt;/a&gt; found on the &lt;a href=\"Level%204%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;forth level&lt;/a&gt; of the original \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Game%29\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;\". He always awaits with his minions.\nHe looks like a Burning Dead except with pale yellow patches.\nDiablo III.\nBlackash is one of the Unique monsters to reappear during &lt;a href=\"The%20Darkening%20of%20Tristram\"&gt;The Darkening of Tristram&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "6849", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6849", "title": "Blackbog's Sharp", "text": "Blackbog's Sharp is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Cinquedeas\"&gt;Cinquedeas&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nA solid dagger for a &lt;a href=\"Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; specializing in &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Skills\"&gt;Poison Skills&lt;/a&gt;, Blackbog's Sharp not only deals a lot of poison damage on its own, but gives a large amount of skill points to the entire poison branch of the &lt;a href=\"Poison%20and%20Bone%20Spells\"&gt;Poison and Bone Spells&lt;/a&gt; tab. While powerful if its venom is allowed to deal its full damage, Blackbog's Sharp is notably less useful against enemies immune to poison.\nStats.\nOne-Hand Damage: 30 To 76\nRequired Level 38\nRequired Strength: 25\nRequired Dexterity: 88\nDurability: 24\nDagger Class - "}
{"id": "41315", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41315", "title": "Blackbog's Sharp (Diablo III Ethereal)", "text": "Blackbog's Sharp is an &lt;a href=\"Ethereal%20Items%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Ethereal&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Dagger\"&gt;Dagger&lt;/a&gt; for the &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It can drop at any level during &lt;a href=\"Season%23Season%2024\"&gt;season&lt;/a&gt; 24. If a player collects all 21 unique Ethereals before season 24 concludes, this item will become available as a &lt;a href=\"transmogrification\"&gt;transmogrification&lt;/a&gt; option."}
