{"id": "6467", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6467", "title": "Blackoak Shield (Diablo II)", "text": "Blackoak Shield is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Luna\"&gt;Luna&lt;/a&gt;, a type of &lt;a href=\"Shields\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt; from \"\".\nAlthough it has a lower &lt;a href=\"block\"&gt;block&lt;/a&gt; rate compared to other, smaller shields, Blackoak Shield has a number of other interesting properties that make it worth using. \nPerhaps the most noticeable ability of Blackoak Shield is its large potential of absorbing &lt;a href=\"Cold\"&gt;Cold&lt;/a&gt; damage. It may have the potential for being able to absorb the most Cold damage out of any item, which when combined with other &lt;a href=\"Cold%20Resist\"&gt;Cold Resist&lt;/a&gt; equipment (e.g. &lt;a href=\"Hawkmail\"&gt;Hawkmail&lt;/a&gt;, etc.), could help boost a player's Cold Resist to very effective levels as far as &lt;a href=\"Difficulty\"&gt;Difficulty&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlong the same lines, although Blackoak Shield does not make a player &lt;a href=\"Cannot%20be%20Frozen\"&gt;immune to being frozen&lt;/a&gt;, it does half freeze time, which is useful as freeze time increases to very long time periods in later game.\nAlthough Blackoak Shield does not have as high chance to block, it does have quite a &lt;a href=\"Faster%20Block%20Rate\"&gt;Faster Block Rate&lt;/a&gt; bonus. It also has a small chance of casting &lt;a href=\"Weaken\"&gt;Weaken&lt;/a&gt; when struck; not an intensely useful ability, it is handy when surrounded by legions of monsters that are physical attackers.\nStats.\nDefense: (322-372) \nRequired Level: 61\nRequired Strength: 100\nDurability: 129\nChance to Block:\nPaladin &lt;a href=\"Smite\"&gt;Smite&lt;/a&gt; Damage: 17 To 29"}
