{"id": "20749", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20749", "title": "Blacksmith", "text": "Blacksmiths forge, salvage, and repair gear.\nNotable Blacksmiths.\n\"Main article: \nBlacksmiths have appeared in every \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20series\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;\" game. While they perform similar functions, the games' handling of them differs between entries.\nDiablo I.\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20I\"&gt;Diablo I&lt;/a&gt;\", &lt;a href=\"Griswold\"&gt;Griswold&lt;/a&gt; is the only blacksmith in the game. He sells and repair equipment.\nDiablo II.\n\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\" introduced an &lt;a href=\"act\"&gt;act&lt;/a&gt; structure to the series. Each act has its own blacksmith, listed as follows, who sells and repair equipment:\nDiablo Immortal.\nSimilar to \"Diablo II\", a different blacksmith is located in each zone in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". They are listed as follows:\nDiablo III.\nFrom a gameplay standpoint, &lt;a href=\"Haedrig%20Eamon\"&gt;Haedrig Eamon&lt;/a&gt; is the only blacksmith of note in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". He is obtained in the game's &lt;a href=\"Act%20I%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;first act&lt;/a&gt;, and remains at the player's side throughout the game.\nDiablo IV.\nBlacksmiths return in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\", being found on towns nearly every town. Similarly to \"Diablo III\", blacksmiths can repair and upgrade equipment, but cannot craft gear.\nThey are also able to well salvage unwanted gear into raw materials; players get different materials depending on the rarity of the equipment salvaged. Players can now mark items as \"junk\", and have an option at blacksmiths to salvage all junk items. There is also a \"salvage all items\" option, which will automatically target all types of gear up to rare; &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;Legendary&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;Unique Items&lt;/a&gt; won't be included in this option."}
