{"id": "22999", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22999", "title": "Blackthorne's Battlegear", "text": "Blackthorne's Battlegear\u00a0(previously Blackthorne's Armor) is an &lt;a href=\"Set%20Items\"&gt;item set&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis set is named for Baron &lt;a href=\"Blackthorne\"&gt;Blackthorne&lt;/a&gt;, a commander who fought against &lt;a href=\"King%20Leoric\"&gt;King Leoric&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe set requires a character level of 60, and is fit for any class. Its drop rate is higher than that of other sets, so it is very likely to be the first set obtained by a character. Prior to patch 2.1, the set itself was focused on survival, being useful for starting the higher difficulties. As of 2.1, it has become more balanced.\nPieces.\nThe set consists of five pieces, all of which can be adapted for any class. The set can be completed with any four of them.\nSet Bonuses:\nThe latter bonus\u00a0protects players from both Molten lava streams and post-death Molten explosions.\nTrivia.\n(\"&lt;a href=\"http%3A//www.mobygames.com/game/blackthorne\"&gt;Blackthorne&lt;/a&gt;\" is the name of one of Blizzard's earliest games, a platform shooter released in 1994."}
{"id": "23002", "revid": "25771421", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=23002", "title": "Blackthorne's Duncraig Cross", "text": "Blackthorne's Duncraig Cross is an Amulet piece of the &lt;a href=\"Blackthorne%27s%20Battlegear\"&gt;Blackthorne's Battlegear&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Set%20Items\"&gt;set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It requires &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 60 to drop.\nPrior to patch 2.1, it had a guaranteed &lt;a href=\"Life\"&gt;Life&lt;/a&gt; %, &lt;a href=\"Attack%20Speed\"&gt;Attack Speed&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Life%20on%20Hit\"&gt;Life on Hit&lt;/a&gt; bonus allotments, which many players considered a mixed blessing; while it offered a greater degree of longevity, it was lacking the proper damaging power to be worth using in endgame builds, with or without &lt;a href=\"Enchanting\"&gt;enchanting&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "23004", "revid": "25771421", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=23004", "title": "Blackthorne's Jousting Mail", "text": "Blackthorne's Jousting Mail is a\u00a0Pants piece of the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Blackthorne%27s%20Battlegear\"&gt;Blackthorne's Battlegear&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Set%20Items\"&gt;set&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It requires\u00a0&lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt;\u00a060 to drop.\nPrior to patch 2.1, these were the only Pants in game with the guaranteed &lt;a href=\"Life\"&gt;Life&lt;/a&gt; % and &lt;a href=\"Life%20on%20Hit\"&gt;Life on Hit&lt;/a&gt; affixes \"no other\" items for this slot could roll. In exchange, if one wanted to make these fit in an endgame build, one of the Primary affixes had to be be &lt;a href=\"Enchanting\"&gt;enchanted&lt;/a&gt;.\nAs of patch 2.7.0, it also has a random &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20Damage\"&gt;Elemental Damage&lt;/a&gt; affix."}
