{"id": "4886", "revid": "48080954", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4886", "title": "Blade Fury", "text": "Blade Fury is an &lt;a href=\"Assassin\"&gt;Assassin&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"Using this skill, the Assassin throws several small blades, shredding her enemies with a barrage of metal. \"\nGeneral Information.\nSynergies.\nThis \"trap\" is very different from most other skills in the tab. Instead of setting up some sort of automatically-firing turret device, this skill causes the Assassin to actively damage enemies by throwing blades. This skill is also a weapon-based attack, receiving 3/4 the damage of the assassin's wielded weapon (3/8 if the weapon is two-handed) as well as almost any on-hit attributes other than Chance to Cast on Attack.\nBlade Fury does not use up durability from the Assassin's weapon, so using an &lt;a href=\"ethereal\"&gt;ethereal&lt;/a&gt; weapon results in more damage with no drawbacks. It also has a fixed rate of fire, thus working better with &lt;a href=\"Fade\"&gt;Fade&lt;/a&gt; than &lt;a href=\"Burst%20of%20Speed\"&gt;Burst of Speed&lt;/a&gt;. Blade Fury relies on &lt;a href=\"attack%20rating\"&gt;attack rating&lt;/a&gt;, but it does not provide any AR bonus.\nThe damage listed on the skill is treated as +min/max damage that ignores the 3/4 (or 3/8) penalty, rather than added straight onto the final damage like the character screen implies, so it does receive bonus from STR, DEX and off-weapon Enhanced Damage. The \"Damage +x\" mod on &lt;a href=\"Grief%20Rune%20Word\"&gt;Grief Rune Word&lt;/a&gt; and some other weapons do not work with Blade Fury. If the assassin is wielding a claw, &lt;a href=\"Claw%20Mastery\"&gt;Claw Mastery&lt;/a&gt;'s damage and critical bonus is applied, but attack rating bonus is not. Many of these are not correctly displayed on the character screen.\nThe assassin can utilize this skill along with a weapon that has good &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20Blow\"&gt;Crushing Blow&lt;/a&gt; to safely dispatch adversaries too dangerous to approach (such as &lt;a href=\"Extra%20Strong\"&gt;Extra Strong&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"Cursed\"&gt;Cursed&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Enchanted\"&gt;Lightning Enchanted&lt;/a&gt; unique monsters). It is possible to make a viable character build around this skill, which focuses on off-weapon Enhanced Damage from auras and equipment to effectively boost damage.\nThis skill is very different from most other skills in the game. Nearly every other skill provides a +% enhanced damage to your attack, and off-weapon +% enhanced damage is added to the skill-based +% enhanced damage before being multiplied with the weapon damage. This skill adds a + damage to your attack, then is then multiplied by off-weapon +% enhanced damage. If you want to build an Assassin around this skill, you want to put as many +% enhanced damage jewels in your helmet, armor, and shield as you can, hire a Might mercenary, then pump this skill to maximum.\nSkill Progression.\nMinimum Mana to Cast: 3\n+3/4 Weapon Damage"}
{"id": "14161", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14161", "title": "Blade Fury Sin", "text": "This build utilizes the Blade Fury skill, a ranged attack that takes into account the melee weapon damage and certain properties that transfer to the attack such as Crushing Blow. This build can be a lot of fun to play and it is possible, if properly built, to complete Uber Tristram solo.\nSkills.\nSkills to max out:.\n&lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Warrior\"&gt;Shadow Warrior&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Master\"&gt;Shadow Master&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=\"Blade%20Fury\"&gt;Blade Fury&lt;/a&gt; is a ranged attack, and having something to get in the way will help.&lt;a href=\"Mind%20Blast\"&gt;Mind Blast&lt;/a&gt;: Stuns opponents as well as having a chance to convert non-unique monsters.&lt;a href=\"Venom\"&gt;Venom&lt;/a&gt;: Add poison damage to the attack. Keep in mind that all poison damage has a duration of 0.8 seconds, so other sources of poison aside from the Venom skill will be nerfed badly.\n&lt;a href=\"Blade%20Fury\"&gt;Blade Fury&lt;/a&gt;: Although the bonus damage added by maxing out this skill may not initially look like much, it is added to base weapon damage and can be multiplied many times over by off-weapon ED% such as Fortitude or Laying of Hands, Might auras, etc. This can easily result in thousands more damage vs. placing only a single point in Blade Fury. (This increased damage will not show up properly on the LCS, \"Lying Character Sheet\", but it has been stated to work this way on Blizzard's Arreat Summit site and has been confirmed to work this way in independent testing.)\nSecondary Skills.\n&lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Shadows\"&gt;Cloak of Shadows&lt;/a&gt;: 7-10 points will make it more helpful in defense bonuses and to damage/evade foes without mob retaliation&lt;a href=\"Blade%20Sentinel\"&gt;Blade Sentinel&lt;/a&gt;: A single point should be enough.&lt;a href=\"Blade%20Shield\"&gt;Blade Shield&lt;/a&gt;: A single point should be enough, but more can be added. Keep in mind that this causes the player's weapon to deteriorate, so an ethereal weapon, unless it has a repair mod or is Indestructible will suffer weapon degradation.&lt;a href=\"Claw%20Mastery\"&gt;Claw Mastery&lt;/a&gt;: A single point can return benefits, especially if there are +skills to this tree.&lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Block\"&gt;Weapon Block&lt;/a&gt;: If the Assassin will be employing two claws, this will allow a character to block even magical attacks. Due to diminishing returns, it is suggested not to invest more than ten points in this skill.&lt;a href=\"Death%20Sentry\"&gt;Death Sentry&lt;/a&gt;: Fires lightning or launches Corpse Explosion.&lt;a href=\"Fire%20Bomb\"&gt;Fire Bomb&lt;/a&gt;: Add some points to this to increase the number of shots a Death Sentry can deliver before expiring."}
