{"id": "9259", "revid": "171752", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9259", "title": "Double Strike", "text": "Gives X% chance to swing with both weapons on every melee attack."}
{"id": "3548", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3548", "title": "Double Swing", "text": "Double Swing is a &lt;a href=\"Barbarian%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;Barbarian&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"A Barbarian warrior learns to fight with a weapon in each hand; after all, are not two weapons better than one? A young Barbarian learns to use both hands independently of each other, striking simultaneous blows at separate targets. As his talent grows in this skill, he attacks with increasing control and accuracy. \"\nGeneral Information.\nSynergies.\nDouble Strike allows the user to strike quickly at two different enemies (or one enemy twice, if only one is in range).\u00a0Double Swing basically doubles the Barbarian's\u00a0total\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Attack%20Speed\"&gt;Attack Speed&lt;/a&gt;, as well as chances of threatening targets\u00a0with &lt;a href=\"Open%20Wounds\"&gt;Open Wounds&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Crushing%20Blow\"&gt;Crushing Blow&lt;/a&gt; etc.\u00a0\nWhile this skill is quite powerful (it can be effective even in &lt;a href=\"Hell%20difficulty\"&gt;Hell difficulty&lt;/a&gt;), it is often overshadowed by the similar yet stronger skill, especially when synergy skills are considered. However, some players may opt to continue using Double Swing as their main form of offense, if the reduction of attack speed is too much, or the increased speed causes increased confusion or lag. The two skills can be used in conjunction as well, though if this is to be the case, it's not recommended to place more than a couple points into Frenzy, as the benefits per stack drop sharply after the first two hits.\nAt default level, it costs 2 Mana to use Double Swing. As the Barbarian puts points into this skill, the Mana cost levels off, eventually reaching 0. This negates any problems with a Mana shortage, making Double Swing a 'free, upgraded' version of the Barbarian's basic Attack that he can switch to should he need to strike quickly to regain his Mana using &lt;a href=\"Mana%20Steal\"&gt;Mana Leech&lt;/a&gt;. As Mana cost listed gives two attacks, cost per hit is even lower."}
{"id": "38833", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38833", "title": "Double Swing (Diablo IV)", "text": "Double Swing\u00a0is a Fury skill used by\u00a0\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\", based on its &lt;a href=\"Double%20Swing\"&gt;classic variant&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nWhen used, hits a short-ranged cone to the left and right of the Barbarian, damaging all enemies caught in each. The cones intersect in front of the Barbarian. Damage dealt is same for both weapons, averaged even if they are drastically different.\nRequires two &lt;a href=\"One-Handed\"&gt;One-Handed&lt;/a&gt; weapons to be equipped and switches to these when used.\nCounts as Warlord skill."}
{"id": "3550", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3550", "title": "Double Throw", "text": "Double Throw is a &lt;a href=\"Barbarian%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;Barbarian&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"To a Barbarian, fighting with two weapons is considered a fairly simple feat. Not so simple is mastering the art of throwing two weapons simultaneously and accurately. Many young Barbarians are eager to learn this skill, for they will tell you it is concrete proof that they have risen to greatness as a warrior. In truth, they use this skill in tavern games almost as often as they do in battle, winning wagers from unsuspecting drunkards. \"\nGeneral Information.\nSynergies.\nThe ranged cousin to Double Swing, the Barbarian throws both weapons at his target, with a brief delay between the first and second throw. Additional &lt;a href=\"Attack%20Rating\"&gt;Attack Rating&lt;/a&gt; and damage are granted.\nWhile this does seem to create a build focused around dual wielding throwing weaponry, ultimately, he cannot fare as well as the &lt;a href=\"Amazon\"&gt;Amazon&lt;/a&gt; does, thanks to her added &lt;a href=\"elemental%20damage\"&gt;elemental damage&lt;/a&gt; on most skills vs. the Barbarian's physical only throws. It must be compensated by items, such as &lt;a href=\"Gimmershred\"&gt;Gimmershred&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Demon%27s%20Arch\"&gt;Demon's Arch&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhile Double Throw is not as potent as some of the Barbarian's other skills, it is a prerequisite towards the powerful\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Frenzy%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;Frenzy&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0skill.\nSkill Progression.\nMana Cost: 2"}
