{"id": "43296", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43296", "title": "Dra'yev", "text": "Dra'yev, Twin Souls is a &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt; created by &lt;a href=\"Skarn\"&gt;Skarn&lt;/a&gt;, through fusing the &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt;s of the brothers &lt;a href=\"Dravec\"&gt;Dravec&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Tayev\"&gt;Tayev&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nThroughout his training at the &lt;a href=\"Sanctified%20Earth%20Monastery\"&gt;Sanctified Earth Monastery&lt;/a&gt;, Dravec's bitterness and anomie were only calmed by his brother. Tayev. Tayev's &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt; ensured Dravec would never know calm again. The brothers were reunited after Dravec pledged his soul to Skarn, Lord of Damnation, who cruelly granted Dravec's wish by fusing the two into a demonic monstrosity.\nAfter delivering a &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt; shard to &lt;a href=\"Skarn\"&gt;Skarn&lt;/a&gt;, Skarn fulfilled his pact with Dravec in a twisted manner by fusing Dravec's soul with his brother's, creating a new demon from the fusion. Skarn then left the demon behind to delay &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt; while he retreated to &lt;a href=\"Realm%20of%20Damnation\"&gt;his domain&lt;/a&gt;. The demon was killed by the hero(es).\nIn-game.\nThe Twin Souls is the final boss of the &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Tundra\"&gt;Frozen Tundra&lt;/a&gt; zone of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It is fought in the &lt;a href=\"Unformed%20Land\"&gt;Unformed Land&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Hall%20of%20Ancients\"&gt;Hall of Ancients&lt;/a&gt;, which is located in the &lt;a href=\"Ruins%20of%20Sescheron\"&gt;Ruins of Sescheron&lt;/a&gt;.\nAs a clue to its origin, the demon looks like a mangled fusion of 2 men. The main body seems to belong to Tayev, with Dravec's torso and left hand protuding from its chest. Dravec's whip is fused to his left hand, forming a sideways tail.\nPhase 2.\nAt of its total &lt;a href=\"life\"&gt;life&lt;/a&gt;, Dra'yev splits into its component halves. Both Dravec and Tayev act as independent units, with their specific attacks.\nPhase 3.\nWhen either Dravec or Tayev have been injured to of their total life, they merge back together for the next phase. The battle begins with a nova."}
