{"id": "4869", "revid": "1687225", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4869", "title": "Dragon Flight", "text": "Dragon Flight is an &lt;a href=\"Assassin\"&gt;Assassin&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"After years of disciplined physical conditioning, an Assassin can develop the ability to move faster than the eye can follow in one quick burst. Using this skill, she lunges at her target and delivers a devastating kick.\"\nGeneral Information.\nSynergies.\nThis ability is a &lt;a href=\"Finishing%20Move\"&gt;Finishing Move&lt;/a&gt;, unleashing one charge from each of the &lt;a href=\"Charge-up%20Skill\"&gt;Charge-up Skill&lt;/a&gt;s as well as adding its own benefit. If any charge is consumes, this skill always hits.\nDragon Flight s the user and any minions to the monster they clicked on. In addition to requiring a monster, it requires a clear line of sight; in other words, trees, walls and other obstacles prevent a Dragon Flight beyond it. Dragon flight is useful for escaping from more dangerous enemies. \nDragon flight is useful for maintaining charges from charged moves by cutting down time between engagements, and is particularly useful when used in conjunction with the &lt;a href=\"Mosaic%20Rune%20Word\"&gt;Mosaic Rune Word&lt;/a&gt;s for this reason."}
