{"id": "40634", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40634", "title": "Drian", "text": "Drian was a soldier stationed at &lt;a href=\"Bastion%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Bastion's Keep&lt;/a&gt;. He was married to &lt;a href=\"Nikola\"&gt;Nikola&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen &lt;a href=\"Azmodan\"&gt;Azmodan&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Siege%20of%20Bastion%27s%20Keep\"&gt;besieged&lt;/a&gt; the fortress, Drian urged Nikola to flee south, but upon his confirmation that he wouldn't flee with her, she refused to flee. She told him to put a &lt;a href=\"swords\"&gt;sword&lt;/a&gt; in her hand, and she'd fight alongside him.\nDuring the siege, demons invaded the keep's main &lt;a href=\"Bastion%27s%20Keep%20Stronghold\"&gt;stronghold&lt;/a&gt;, but they were defeated by &lt;a href=\"The%20Nephalem\"&gt;The Nephalem&lt;/a&gt;. Afterwards, Nikola asked Drian how he was able to face the &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s. He said that he did it for her.\nEventually, the demons were driven from the keep, though the fighting continued outside. Nikola stated that when the siege was over, they should have children. Drian stated \"that sounds wonderful. I think I\u2019m needed back on the wall.\"\nWhen The Nephalem departed the keep to confront Azmodan, Drian complained how he wasn't able to be there. Nikola said \"good. You could use some sleep.\" Drian responded that he wasn't tired, before &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sexual_intercourse\"&gt;catching on&lt;/a&gt;.\nDrian was apparently killed by &lt;a href=\"Adria\"&gt;Adria&lt;/a&gt; after she revealed her true allegiance to &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;, turning on the Keep's defenders."}
