{"id": "1446", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1446", "title": "Drognan", "text": "Drognan is a resident of &lt;a href=\"Lut%20Gholein\"&gt;Lut Gholein&lt;/a&gt;. \nBiography.\nA member of the &lt;a href=\"Vizjerei%20Clan\"&gt;Vizjerei Clan&lt;/a&gt;, Drognan spent many years practicing magic. His reputation gave &lt;a href=\"Elzix\"&gt;Elzix&lt;/a&gt; pause, ensuring the man would never try to cheat him.\nDrognan ran a shop in Lut Gholein, known for its arcane wonders.\nThe Secret of the Vizjerei.\nAfter the &lt;a href=\"Darkening%20of%20Tristram%20%28Event%29\"&gt;Darkening of Tristram&lt;/a&gt;, Drognan was confronted by &lt;a href=\"Jazreth\"&gt;Jazreth&lt;/a&gt;; one of his fellow Vizjerei. Drognan believed that he'd perished in &lt;a href=\"Tristram\"&gt;Tristram&lt;/a&gt;, but clearly, Jazreth had survived. However, he seemed insane, so Drognan dismissed much of what he said. However, he was able to talk his way into Lut Gholein's palace, and no-one saw him afterwards. He feared that Jazreth had found something in the palace that had led to his doom.\nTroubles arose in the desert after the arrival of the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Wanderer\"&gt;Dark Wanderer&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Jerhyn\"&gt;Jerhyn&lt;/a&gt; came to Drognan, seeking his advice. Drognan advised him to close the port and put the town under strict watch. However, this didn't stop a creature from entering the city and killing a number of people, even after being confined to the sewers. Jerhyn and &lt;a href=\"Fara\"&gt;Fara&lt;/a&gt; discussed the matter, and from his studies, Drognan concluded that the creature was &lt;a href=\"Radament%20the%20Fallen\"&gt;Radament the Fallen&lt;/a&gt;.\nDrognan greeted a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20II\"&gt;group of heroes&lt;/a&gt; who were in pursuit of the Dark Wanderer. They slew Radament, passing on the details to Drognan. He concluded that Radament had been intent on reviving his own mummified corpse with the flesh of the living; a very unusual state of affairs for an &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt;. He wondered if there was a greater power at work.\nAfterwards, an eclipse occurred, plunging &lt;a href=\"Aranoch\"&gt;Aranoch&lt;/a&gt; into unnatural darkness. Drognan's research led him to discover that a similar eclipse had occurred several hundred years ago; that desert dwelling snake-demons had errected an altar, which caused the sun to go black. He believed that both eclipses were the work of &lt;a href=\"Claw%20Viper\"&gt;Claw Viper&lt;/a&gt;s. In this, he was correct, and the heroes were able to restore light to the land by slaying the creatures.\nAfter this, Drognan told the heroes of his research into the location of the &lt;a href=\"Tomb%20of%20Tal%20Rasha\"&gt;Tomb of Tal Rasha&lt;/a&gt;. While he was unsure of the tomb's location, he believed that a clue could be found in the &lt;a href=\"Arcane%20Sanctuary\"&gt;Arcane Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;. He told the heroes to speak with Jerhyn, stating that he might be aware of a secret entrance. They gained entrance, and encountered The Summoner, whom Drognan recognised as Jazreth. He suspected that he had been possessed by &lt;a href=\"Horazon\"&gt;Horazon&lt;/a&gt;'s spirit, and told the heroes to put an end to his tortured existence.\nThe heroes were able to use clues found in the Sanctuary to find the Tomb of Tal Rasha. However, they were too late, as Diablo had already freed &lt;a href=\"Baal\"&gt;Baal&lt;/a&gt;. He told the heroes to travel east to &lt;a href=\"Kurast\"&gt;Kurast&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nDrognan is a non-player character who resides in Act 2, in the town of &lt;a href=\"Lut%20Gholein\"&gt;Lut Gholein&lt;/a&gt;. Besides acting as a researcher searching for &lt;a href=\"Tal%20Rasha%27s%20Tomb\"&gt;Tal Rasha's Tomb&lt;/a&gt; (the end level in Act 2), he is also a merchant of &lt;a href=\"Scroll%20of%20Town%20Portal\"&gt;town portal scroll&lt;/a&gt;s as well as a variety of magical &lt;a href=\"staves\"&gt;staves&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe is a member of the &lt;a href=\"Vizjerei%20Clan\"&gt;Vizjerei Clan&lt;/a&gt;, however prefers to study the darker magic of its teachings. Drognan is also a researcher of &lt;a href=\"Horazon\"&gt;Horazon&lt;/a&gt; and tries to remove &lt;a href=\"Bartuc\"&gt;Bartuc&lt;/a&gt;'s armor from Norrec Vizharan in &lt;a href=\"Richard%20A.%20Knaak\"&gt;Richard A. Knaak&lt;/a&gt;'s book &lt;a href=\"Legacy%20of%20Blood\"&gt;Legacy of Blood&lt;/a&gt;. He also is an old and wise Vizjerei who lives in a house that Horazon lived in.\nDialogue.\nGossip about Drognan.\nSome of the other locals give their thoughts concerning Drognan.\nPersonality and Traits.\nA white-bearded man of few and private words, not many have even heard Drognan speak. If he does, it is for a good reason, and when he does, it's in a blunt and honest manner.\nDrognan is well versed in the history of the &lt;a href=\"Horadrim\"&gt;Horadrim&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Prime%20Evils\"&gt;Prime Evils&lt;/a&gt;. Even in his old age, Drognan is still able to use some &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "48654", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48654", "title": "Dross Eater", "text": "s are a specie of &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s found within the &lt;a href=\"Realm%20of%20Damnation\"&gt;Realm of Damnation&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nThe bellicose dross eaters appear native to the Realm of Damnation. They flood lava banks at the slightest presence of any trespassers including other demons, and breach the molten surface of their home to spew gobs of &lt;a href=\"fire\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt; that cling to the skin.\nIn-game.\n appear as &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". They can be found at the &lt;a href=\"Molten%20Egress\"&gt;Molten Egress&lt;/a&gt; of the Realm of Damnation. They attack with claw swipes at melee. At a distance, they spit out fast-moving globs of lava that leave &lt;a href=\"damage%20over%20time%23Burn\"&gt;burning&lt;/a&gt; trails in their wakes and can ricochet between obstacles."}
{"id": "38498", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38498", "title": "Drowned", "text": "The Drowned are &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; which emerge from &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;'s coastlines to drag their victims to a watery grave. They currently dominate the entire coastline of &lt;a href=\"Scosglen\"&gt;Scosglen&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nThe Drowned are led by &lt;a href=\"the%20Lady\"&gt;the Lady&lt;/a&gt;, and have always been a threat to Sanctuary. They come from bodies washing ashore (such as from ships lost at sea), bloating in the midday sun. After the first moonless night, after all other omens have passed, the Drowned will appear. When they attack, they infect the shores like a disease, and with them comes a thick brackish fog that encroaches in from the shoreline. Every time they attack, there's the unyielding tolling of bells, a reminder to the living that the Drowned were rallying and coming for them. They have also been observed to carry strange idols during their attacks.\nHistory.\nThe Drowned appear to have existed for quite awhile. They hoard the spoils of their raids in their hoards beneath the sea. These contain the relics of long-lost cultures.\nBy the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Enmity\"&gt;Great Enmity&lt;/a&gt;, the Drowned had not been seen in generations, and most didn't believe they existed. Nevertheless, they did remain in the cultural zeitgeist, as they were regarded as \"terrors\" that existed in the night that would come to kidnap people. Villagers would tell their children that if they didn't behave, the Drowned would come and take them.\nUnfortunately for the people of Sanctuary, the Drowned \"were\" real, and came to dominate the entire coast of &lt;a href=\"Scosglen\"&gt;Scosglen&lt;/a&gt;. \nIn-game.\nDiablo Immortal.\nThe Drowned appear in the &lt;a href=\"Age%20of%20Falling%20Towers\"&gt;Age of Falling Towers&lt;/a&gt; update of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". Here, they are the &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; remnants of Inari and Lilin that killed each other during the &lt;a href=\"Mutinous%20Concord\"&gt;Mutinous Concord&lt;/a&gt;. They are the major enemies in the &lt;a href=\"Dread%20Reaver\"&gt;Dread Reaver&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"dungeon\"&gt;dungeon&lt;/a&gt;.\nDiablo IV.\nThe Drowned appear as enemies in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\". They are one of the game's \"monster families.\" Befitting their name, they are found in the game's coastal areas.\nDevelopment.\nThe Drowned were first showcased at &lt;a href=\"BlizzCon\"&gt;BlizzCon&lt;/a&gt; 2019.\nThe Drowned are an example of the environmental storytelling used in \"Diablo IV\", where their attacks are water and ship-themed. While players can obtain more information on the Drowned via quests and &lt;a href=\"tomes\"&gt;tomes&lt;/a&gt;, the idea is that the player should be able to understand the Drowned's relationship to the sea just by looking at them."}
