{"id": "18932", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18932", "title": "Drowned Temple", "text": "The Drowned Temple (formerly known as the Sarceum Emporis) is a location in &lt;a href=\"Act%20I%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act I&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". \nLore.\nThe temple is located near the &lt;a href=\"Festering%20Woods\"&gt;Festering Woods&lt;/a&gt;, and north of the &lt;a href=\"Fields%20of%20Misery\"&gt;Fields of Misery&lt;/a&gt;. Originally called the Sarceum Emporis, it was the most sacred &lt;a href=\"nephalem\"&gt;nephalem&lt;/a&gt; temple constructed; a site where, according to legend, &lt;a href=\"angel\"&gt;angel&lt;/a&gt;s would come to impart their wisdom to the nephalem.\nOnly nephalem may enter the temple, though &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;s may enter alongside nephalem.\nHistory.\nThe temple was constructed before the &lt;a href=\"Sin%20War%20%28Event%29\"&gt;Sin War&lt;/a&gt;. \nAfter &lt;a href=\"Inarius\"&gt;Inarius&lt;/a&gt; altered the &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt;, nephalem children began to be born weak and suffer short lives (a prelude to the nephalem becoming human). The &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Nereza\"&gt;Nereza&lt;/a&gt; promised to restore their power, but instead turned them into misshapen creatures, and sent them to war against the nephalem of the temple. The nephalem were killed, but even as &lt;a href=\"ghost\"&gt;ghost&lt;/a&gt;s, they continued to play out their war. Legends of the event found their way into mortal &lt;a href=\"tome\"&gt;tome&lt;/a&gt;s.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231285\"&gt;1285&lt;/a&gt;, a shard of &lt;a href=\"El%27druin\"&gt;El'druin&lt;/a&gt; crashed into the temple. It was sought after by both the &lt;a href=\"Coven\"&gt;Coven&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"The%20Nephalem\"&gt;The Nephalem&lt;/a&gt;. Unable to enter the temple, &lt;a href=\"Maghda\"&gt;Maghda&lt;/a&gt; waited for The Nephalem to unseal the temple, so that her forces could move in to retrieve the shard. Arriving at the temple's entrance alongside &lt;a href=\"Leah\"&gt;Leah&lt;/a&gt;, The Nephalem was confrontd by &lt;a href=\"Alaric\"&gt;Alaric&lt;/a&gt;, who was aware of The Nephalem's birthright, even if they were not. He bid them collect keys from outlying tombs to gain entrance. Completing this task, Alaric opened the temple's entrance. He told The Nephalem to enter and defeat the guardians within.\nThe Nephalem succeeded, and gained access to the shard. Maghda's forces launched their ambush, but were defeated. With that, the heroes returned to &lt;a href=\"New%20Tristram\"&gt;New Tristram&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nThe temple features in the &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Broken%20Blade\"&gt;The Broken Blade&lt;/a&gt;.\" To enter the temple, players must find two keys; one at &lt;a href=\"Warrior%27s%20Rest\"&gt;Warrior's Rest&lt;/a&gt;, and one at &lt;a href=\"Crypt%20of%20the%20Ancients\"&gt;Crypt of the Ancients&lt;/a&gt;. \nInside players can find a &lt;a href=\"Super%20Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;superunique&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0&lt;a href=\"skeleton\"&gt;skeleton&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0called\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Ezek%20the%20Prophet\"&gt;Ezek the Prophet&lt;/a&gt; and the second shard of &lt;a href=\"El%27druin\"&gt;El'druin&lt;/a&gt;.\nApart of the quest this area is completely devoid of enemies."}
