{"id": "9092", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9092", "title": "Dungeon randomization", "text": "Dungeon randomization is one of the features of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\". Instead of playing in the same world-layout over and over again, Diablo II generates random maps of areas, making every new game 'unique', in a way. Though the layout of the areas might differ, they still 'connect' in the same way. For instance: the &lt;a href=\"Cold%20Plains\"&gt;Cold Plains&lt;/a&gt; might look different on different but it still connects the &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Moor\"&gt;Blood Moor&lt;/a&gt; with the &lt;a href=\"Burial%20Grounds\"&gt;Burial Grounds&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Stony%20Field\"&gt;Stony Field&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlthough many dungeons and areas have random layouts, some areas will always be the same. Here are some (not all) of the areas with the same layout:"}
