{"id": "4092", "revid": "48648864", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4092", "title": "Dusk Shroud", "text": "Dusk Shroud is a type of &lt;a href=\"Body%20Armor\"&gt;Body Armor&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\", it is the &lt;a href=\"Elite%20Items\"&gt;Elite&lt;/a&gt; version of .\nIt is a favourite amongst casters for its low &lt;a href=\"strength\"&gt;strength&lt;/a&gt; requirement and possibility to have up to 4 sockets, making it a popular body armor for , , or &lt;a href=\"Rune%20Words\"&gt;Rune Words&lt;/a&gt;. Despite its low strength requirement, the best Dusk Shrouds have better defense than even the strongest\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Exceptional%20Items\"&gt;Exceptional&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0quality armor. Characters who have invested more points into strength may be better served using an &lt;a href=\"Archon%20Plate\"&gt;Archon Plate&lt;/a&gt; instead, which grants more defense but still retains the light armor characteristic.\u00a0"}
{"id": "44223", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44223", "title": "Dusk on the Mountain", "text": "Dusk on the Mountain is a campaign &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV%20Quests\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; available in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\". \nIt is automatically initiated in &lt;a href=\"Nevesk\"&gt;Nevesk&lt;/a&gt;, after confirming a new character and watching the prologue introduction. It is followed by the \"&lt;a href=\"Darkness%20Within\"&gt;Darkness Within&lt;/a&gt;\" quest. \nWalkthrough.\nHead towards yellow quest indicator. After entering the town of &lt;a href=\"Nevesk\"&gt;Nevesk&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"The%20Wanderer%20%28Diablo%20IV%29\"&gt;the Wanderer&lt;/a&gt; hears voices coming from a nearby shed. Head towards the yellow indicator to interact with the shed door. After speaking with &lt;a href=\"Oswen\"&gt;Oswen&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Vani\"&gt;Vani&lt;/a&gt;, follow Vani into tavern. On the way she tells the Wanderer that the monk went mad after entering a nearby ruin. Upon entering the tavern, the Wanderer meets the rest of the townsfolks: &lt;a href=\"Isbel\"&gt;Isbel&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Devmir\"&gt;Devmir&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Elenta\"&gt;Elenta&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stanis\"&gt;Stanis&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Tovri\"&gt;Tovri&lt;/a&gt;. After speaking with Vani, the Wanderer then agrees to investigate the &lt;a href=\"Icehowl%20Ruins\"&gt;Icehowl Ruins&lt;/a&gt;. "}
