{"id": "44406", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44406", "title": "Dymdrail, Crawling Woe", "text": " is a member of the &lt;a href=\"Voidwound\"&gt;Voidwound&lt;/a&gt;.\nDymdrail is a creature of shadow, insatiable. Multitudes are located within it, and with each &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt; it devours, it grows in legion.\nBiography.\nLike all the Voidwound, Dymdrail was reshaped by the primordial ages it spent in the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Abyss\"&gt;Black Abyss&lt;/a&gt;. In Dymdrail's case, it was reshaped into a creature of shadow.\nAfter the Voidwound emerged in &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;, Dymdrail established its &lt;a href=\"Hall%20of%20Decadence\"&gt;lair&lt;/a&gt;, somewhere in Sanctuary's eastern hemisphere. Nevertheless, it, and the other Voidwound met with the &lt;a href=\"witch%20circle\"&gt;witch circle&lt;/a&gt;s of the &lt;a href=\"Sharval%20Wilds\"&gt;Sharval Wilds&lt;/a&gt;. It demanded a march of sevenscore &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt;s into its lair as part of a pact. One that failed to be made. Later, Dymdrail and the other Voidwound (save &lt;a href=\"Catarag\"&gt;Catarag&lt;/a&gt;, who was sealed earlier) were tricked by the &lt;a href=\"Untameable%20Wilds\"&gt;Untameable Wilds&lt;/a&gt; circle. The Voidwound were goaded into possessing the &lt;a href=\"Witch\"&gt;Witch&lt;/a&gt;es, but this was a trap, as the Witches used themselves as vessels to carry their demonic hosts to the &lt;a href=\"Voidwound%20Cage\"&gt;Voidwound Cage&lt;/a&gt;. While it cost the circle dearly, Dymdrail and the other Voidwound were successfully imprisoned.\nUncaged.\nAround &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231272\"&gt;1272&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Cult%20of%20Terror\"&gt;Cult of Terror&lt;/a&gt; attacked the Voidwound Cage in order to free its prisoners. They were stymied by &lt;a href=\"Nisza\"&gt;Nisza&lt;/a&gt; \u2014 the current wardkeeper of the Untameable Wilds, but their cage was damaged, causing an explosion that scattered &lt;a href=\"Crimson%20Slag\"&gt;bits of the cage&lt;/a&gt; far and wide. This caused the Voidwound to awake. Dymdrail sent &lt;a href=\"the%20Many\"&gt;the Many&lt;/a&gt; to hunt her, but she received help in the form of &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Rayek\"&gt;Rayek&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Commander%20Kaya\"&gt;Commander Kaya&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nDymdrail is the third Voidwound &lt;a href=\"Helliquary\"&gt;Helliquary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", introduced as part of the &lt;a href=\"Terror%27s%20Tide\"&gt;Terror's Tide&lt;/a&gt; update. It is able to summon &lt;a href=\"Nightmare%20%28monster%29\"&gt;nightmares&lt;/a&gt; and manipulate darkness. "}
