{"id": "1459", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1459", "title": "Eastgate Keep", "text": "Eastgate Keep, otherwise known as Eastgate Monastery, the Rogue Monastery, or Citadel of the Sightless Eye is a structure that guards the passage between &lt;a href=\"Khanduras\"&gt;Khanduras&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Aranoch\"&gt;Aranoch&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nEarly History.\nEastgate was constructed by the &lt;a href=\"Sons%20of%20Rakkis\"&gt;Sons of Rakkis&lt;/a&gt; during their crusade against the &lt;a href=\"Western%20Kingdoms\"&gt;West&lt;/a&gt;, the structure serving as a fortified outpost against their enemy's counterattacks. After &lt;a href=\"Rakkis\"&gt;Rakkis&lt;/a&gt;'s previous successes in &lt;a href=\"Aranoch\"&gt;Aranoch&lt;/a&gt;, it was here that he regrouped his forces after the s and people of &lt;a href=\"Ivgorod\"&gt;Ivgorod&lt;/a&gt; proved to be unconquerable. After restoring his men's morale, Rakkis led his forces west, eventually founding &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20%28City%29\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;. Eastgate later fell into abandonment.\nSometime later, the keep received new custodians\u2014a group of rogue &lt;a href=\"Amazon\"&gt;Amazon&lt;/a&gt;s who called themselves the &lt;a href=\"Sisterhood%20of%20the%20Sightless%20Eye\"&gt;Sisterhood of the Sightless Eye&lt;/a&gt;. They used it as their base of operations.\nRecent History.\nThe keep briefly fell to &lt;a href=\"Andariel\"&gt;Andariel&lt;/a&gt; and the Sisterhood was splintered during the &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231264\"&gt;time&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;'s return. However, the cathedral was cleansed by a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20II\"&gt;group of heroes&lt;/a&gt; and Andariel was defeated. &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;Six years later&lt;/a&gt;, survivors of &lt;a href=\"Blackstone%20Village\"&gt;Blackstone Village&lt;/a&gt; fled to Eastgate, where they swore revenge against the &lt;a href=\"Bloodsworn\"&gt;Bloodsworn&lt;/a&gt;. To this end, they were apparently trained by the Rogues.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231286\"&gt;1286&lt;/a&gt;, Eastgate remained under the control of the Rogues, its training grounds humming with the sound of &lt;a href=\"bow\"&gt;bow&lt;/a&gt;strings and battlecries.\nIn-game.\nThe monastery appears in the &lt;a href=\"The%20Sightless%20Eye\"&gt;first act&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\". It is divided into numerous sub-zones."}
