{"id": "8869", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8869", "title": "Eater of Souls", "text": "The Eater of Souls is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Swords\"&gt;sword&lt;/a&gt; found in the \"\" expansion, and is found randomly. This blade gives +50 to &lt;a href=\"Life\"&gt;Life&lt;/a&gt;, and is the only Unique sword to boast both &lt;a href=\"Mana%20Steal\"&gt;Mana&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Life%20Steal\"&gt;Life Steal&lt;/a&gt;. However, when equipped, the player constantly loses Life, making this sword only useful for &lt;a href=\"Barbarian%20%28Hellfire%29\"&gt;Barbarians&lt;/a&gt;, with their greater Vitality and sweeping attack bonus for going without a shield. Even then, they should move fast; if too slow to heal their injuries, the life drain will prove fatal in the labyrinth"}
{"id": "43960", "revid": "51929228", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43960", "title": "Eavesdropper", "text": "Eavesdropper is a &lt;a href=\"Campaign%20Achievements\"&gt;campaign achievement&lt;/a&gt; to read all the Quest lore books in Act II of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nThroughout players' travels across &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;, they will find journal entries, scrolls, diaries, notes and letters written by people both known and unknown. They often record thoughts and feelings of events that occurred in the past, oftentimes even before the time of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Game%29\"&gt;Diablo I&lt;/a&gt;\". They will usually be found at random within certain areas or at a certain spot of the game world, and usually refer to some historical event tied to that general area. Every single one has been voice recorded, which can be heard anytime the player wishes, which convey the mood and emotional state of the author at the time of writing.\nGuard's Orders.\nLocation: &lt;a href=\"Khasim%20Outpost\"&gt;Khasim Outpost&lt;/a&gt;, inside some Imperial Guard Supplies.\n\"\"Captain of the Guard,\"\n\"You are hereby ordered to send a band of your most loyal men to secure the Khasim Outpost.\"\n\"Control of &lt;a href=\"Caldeum\"&gt;the city&lt;/a&gt; hangs by a thread. The commoners are becoming restless, and it is imperative that we subdue them. Remain vigilant, for there may already be &lt;a href=\"The%20Nephalem\"&gt;an outsider&lt;/a&gt; within our borders, looking to stir up trouble\"\"\nProclamation from the Imperial Guard.\nLocation: &lt;a href=\"Caldeum%20Bazaar\"&gt;Caldeum Bazaar&lt;/a&gt;, inside a satchel.\nQuest: &lt;a href=\"A%20Royal%20Audience\"&gt;A Royal Audience&lt;/a&gt;\n\"\"Attention, Subjects of &lt;a href=\"Hakan%20II\"&gt;Emperor Hakan II&lt;/a&gt;:\"\n\"&lt;a href=\"Leah\"&gt;A trespasser&lt;/a&gt; has been sighted in the city sewers. Witnesses describe the suspect as a young woman in a crimson tunic. Reports indicate that she arrived in Caldeum recently along with a party of suspicious travelers. Any information leading to her immediate capture will be handsomely rewarded by His Eminence\"\"\n&lt;a href=\"Imperial%20Guard\"&gt;Imperial Guard&lt;/a&gt;\nMissive to Maghda.\nPart I.\nLocation: &lt;a href=\"Hidden%20Conclave\"&gt;Hidden Conclave&lt;/a&gt;, inside the &lt;a href=\"Howling%20Plateau\"&gt;Howling Plateau&lt;/a&gt;, looted from a Tortured Cultist Courier.\nQuest: &lt;a href=\"Shadows%20in%20the%20Desert\"&gt;Shadows in the Desert&lt;/a&gt;\n\"\"&lt;a href=\"Maghda\"&gt;Maghda&lt;/a&gt;,\"\n\"This &lt;a href=\"The%20Nephalem\"&gt;\"hero\"&lt;/a&gt; means to attack you in &lt;a href=\"Alcarnus\"&gt;Alcarnus&lt;/a&gt;. If I were you, I would set a trap at the &lt;a href=\"Khasim%20Outpost\"&gt;Khasim Outpost&lt;/a&gt;, but I am not you. For all I know, you wish to fail me again and force me to kill you. That would grieve me, though somehow... I think I could manage it\"\"\n&lt;a href=\"Belial\"&gt;Belial&lt;/a&gt;\nPart II.\nLocation: &lt;a href=\"Alcarnus\"&gt;Alcarnus&lt;/a&gt;, looted from a Tortured Coven Minion right outside &lt;a href=\"Lair%20of%20the%20Witch\"&gt;the Lair of the Witch&lt;/a&gt;.\nQuest: &lt;a href=\"City%20of%20Blood\"&gt;City of Blood&lt;/a&gt;\n\"\"&lt;a href=\"Maghda\"&gt;Maghda&lt;/a&gt;,\"\n\"Such sad, sad tales have reached me of your truly abysmal failure to stop the enemy at the &lt;a href=\"Khasim%20Outpost\"&gt;Khasim Outpost&lt;/a&gt;. But at least the enemy's spy has been found. Once we eliminate her and her allies, this obnoxious little world will fall to me... and perhaps you. If you survive\"\"\n&lt;a href=\"Belial\"&gt;Belial&lt;/a&gt;\nDeceiver's Orders.\nPart I.\nLocation: &lt;a href=\"Sewers%20of%20Caldeum\"&gt;Sewers of Caldeum&lt;/a&gt;, on the Envoy of Belial.\n\"\"My exemplary servants,\"\n\"Keep &lt;a href=\"Adria\"&gt;the witch&lt;/a&gt; alive until she talks. Pain will loose her tongue, but only to a point. Remember what happened with the vizier's assistant...? It was a pleasurable time, I admit, but the man had only incoherent babble and bloody strands of pus spilling from his lips by the end\"\"\n&lt;a href=\"Belial\"&gt;Belial&lt;/a&gt;\nPart II.\nLocation: &lt;a href=\"Dahlgur%20Oasis\"&gt;Dahlgur Oasis&lt;/a&gt;, on the Envoy of Belial.\n\"\"Overwhelm &lt;a href=\"The%20Nephalem\"&gt;the enemy&lt;/a&gt; and seize her companions. There is a witch among them and... another... &lt;a href=\"Leah\"&gt;a girl&lt;/a&gt;. Bring them to me along with the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Soulstone\"&gt;Black Soulstone&lt;/a&gt;. They will be searching for the head of &lt;a href=\"Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;Zoltun Kulle&lt;/a&gt;. Scour the oasis for it. Some old sorcery lingers on the skull, and it must be mine\"\"\n&lt;a href=\"Belial\"&gt;Belial&lt;/a&gt;\nPart III.\nLocation: &lt;a href=\"Desolate%20Sands\"&gt;Desolate Sands&lt;/a&gt;, on the Envoy of Belial.\n\"\"Miserable wretches,\"\n\"I have no time for your excuses. &lt;a href=\"Caldeum\"&gt;Caldeum&lt;/a&gt; is on the brink of rebellion, and the enemy is closing in on the &lt;a href=\"The%20Archives%20of%20Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;archives of Zoltun Kulle&lt;/a&gt;. Slaughter her and bring me the &lt;a href=\"Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;mad wizard's&lt;/a&gt; head and the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Soulstone\"&gt;Black Soulstone&lt;/a&gt;, or I shall inflict incomprehensible agony upon the lot of you\"\"\n&lt;a href=\"Belial\"&gt;Belial&lt;/a&gt;\nThe Feared Hero.\nLocation: &lt;a href=\"Stinging%20Winds\"&gt;Stinging Winds&lt;/a&gt;, in a camp on either side of the &lt;a href=\"Khasim%20Outpost\"&gt;Khasim Outpost&lt;/a&gt;.\n\"We camp, lying in wait for a hero of incredible prowess. My gut churns with the suspicion that we are simply fodder. I have heard tales of this hero wading through our ranks, slaughtering us as if we were children. I will not sleep again tonight, I fear\"\n&lt;a href=\"Dark%20Cultist\"&gt;Dark Cultist&lt;/a&gt;\nHunter's Journal.\nPart I.\nLocation: &lt;a href=\"The%20Forgotten%20Ruins\"&gt;The Forgotten Ruins&lt;/a&gt;, looted from the Hunter's Satchel.\n\"\"We are in agreement. &lt;a href=\"Kulle%27s%20Journal\"&gt;Kulle&lt;/a&gt; the renegade must be stopped. He seeks to duplicate the power of &lt;a href=\"Soulstone\"&gt;the stones&lt;/a&gt; and wield it for his own ends. He is obsessed with the powers of &lt;a href=\"High%20Heavens\"&gt;Heaven&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt;. Drawing their attention will only bring doom to us all\"\"\n&lt;a href=\"Iben%20Fahd\"&gt;Iben Fahd&lt;/a&gt;\nPart II.\nLocation: &lt;a href=\"Western%20Channel\"&gt;Western Channel&lt;/a&gt;, looted from the Hunter's Satchel.\n\"\"We set out in one week's time into the &lt;a href=\"Desolate%20Sands\"&gt;Desolate Sands&lt;/a&gt; to search for &lt;a href=\"Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;Kulle's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"The%20Archives%20of%20Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;hidden archives&lt;/a&gt;. None of us have any idea what to expect. How far has Kulle's madness driven him? How much power has he accumulated in his mad quest? I can only hope we are not too late...\"\"\n&lt;a href=\"Iben%20Fahd\"&gt;Iben Fahd&lt;/a&gt;\nPart III.\nLocation: &lt;a href=\"Desolate%20Sands\"&gt;Desolate Sands&lt;/a&gt;, looted from the Hunter's Satchel.\n\"\"We found &lt;a href=\"Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;Kulle's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"The%20Archives%20of%20Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;archives&lt;/a&gt;. They were strangely empty... at first. But Kulle laid traps everywhere. Each step harder than the next. It was foolish to expect otherwise. Kulle has prepared for many years for someone to come for him. Perhaps we are fools, and yet we must push on\"\"\n&lt;a href=\"Iben%20Fahd\"&gt;Iben Fahd&lt;/a&gt;\nPart IV.\nLocation: &lt;a href=\"The%20Storm%20Halls\"&gt;The Storm Halls&lt;/a&gt;, inside &lt;a href=\"The%20Archives%20of%20Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;the Archives of Zoltan Kulle&lt;/a&gt;, looted from the Hunter's Satchel.\n\"\"Try as we might, &lt;a href=\"Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;Kulle&lt;/a&gt; simply cannot be killed. His cursed blood sustains him. He bleeds sand, and his laughter mocks us. There is only one course of action left to us. We will separate his body and his head, and hide the body within &lt;a href=\"Realm%20of%20Shadow\"&gt;the shadow realm&lt;/a&gt;\"\"\n&lt;a href=\"Iben%20Fahd\"&gt;Iben Fahd&lt;/a&gt;\nPart V.\nLocation: &lt;a href=\"The%20Unknown%20Depths\"&gt;The Unknown Depths&lt;/a&gt;, inside &lt;a href=\"The%20Archives%20of%20Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;the Archives of Zoltan Kulle&lt;/a&gt;, looted from the Hunter's Satchel.\n\"\"We will seal the shadow locks with vials of his blood, and we will hide the blood in the desert under eternal guard. I can only hope that the world does not forget of &lt;a href=\"Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;Kulle's&lt;/a&gt; evil, and his blood remains undisturbed &lt;a href=\"Desolate%20Sands\"&gt;beneath the shifting sands&lt;/a&gt;\"\"\n&lt;a href=\"Iben%20Fahd\"&gt;Iben Fahd&lt;/a&gt;\nPart VI.\nLocation: &lt;a href=\"The%20Forgotten%20Ruins\"&gt;The Forgotten Ruins&lt;/a&gt;, dropped by the &lt;a href=\"Ancient%20Guardian\"&gt;Ancient Guardian&lt;/a&gt;.\n\"\"&lt;a href=\"Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;Kulle&lt;/a&gt; mocks my every step. I try to shut him out, but his chattering is ceaseless. He takes joy in taunting me. I will not rise to the bait. I will not give in to him. I long for the silence that will come once I secure his head away\"\"\n&lt;a href=\"Iben%20Fahd\"&gt;Iben Fahd&lt;/a&gt;"}
