{"id": "3132", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3132", "title": "El Rune", "text": "An El rune is a low &lt;a href=\"Runes\"&gt;rune&lt;/a&gt; which can be &lt;a href=\"socket\"&gt;socket&lt;/a&gt;ed into equipment in \"\". El runes are the most common runes in the game, but have a few high level uses, such as the &lt;a href=\"Fortitude%20Rune%20Word\"&gt;Fortitude rune word&lt;/a&gt;, and transmuting low quality armor into normal armor.\nEffects.\nSocketing an item with an El rune increases the item's level requirement to 11, unless it was already higher.\nSources.\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Countess\"&gt;The Countess&lt;/a&gt;'s extra rune drops on any difficulty can include El runes.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Hellforge\"&gt;Hellforge&lt;/a&gt; on normal difficulty has a 1 in 11 chance to drop an El rune as part of its quest reward.\nThe Act 2 Good treasure class has a chance to drop an El rune, as do higher Good treasure classes.\nRune Words.\nEl runes are used in these&lt;a href=\"Rune%20Words\"&gt;rune words&lt;/a&gt;:\nRecipes.\nEl runes are used in two &lt;a href=\"Horadric%20Cube\"&gt;Horadric Cube&lt;/a&gt; recipes."}
{"id": "54229", "revid": "84037", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54229", "title": "Elazar", "text": "Elazar was a &lt;a href=\"Zakarum\"&gt;Zakarum&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nReign of Enmity.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline\"&gt;1336&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"The%20Wanderer%20%28Diablo%20IV%29\"&gt;The Wanderer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Zakarum\"&gt;Zakarum&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Crusaders\"&gt;Crusader&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Ksenia\"&gt;Ksenia&lt;/a&gt; ventured into the depths of the ruins of Rakhat Keep. Ksenia's plan was to cleanse the ruins, freeing the souls of the Fallen &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladins&lt;/a&gt; and purge the evil from &lt;a href=\"Sankekur\"&gt;Sankekur&lt;/a&gt;'s body. The Wanderer and Ksenia managed to exorcise the corrupted ghosts of the Paladins &lt;a href=\"Alodia\"&gt;Alodia&lt;/a&gt;, Elazar, &lt;a href=\"Mathias\"&gt;Mathias&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Retinues\"&gt;Retinues&lt;/a&gt;, who sealed the temple under &lt;a href=\"Carthas\"&gt;Carthas&lt;/a&gt;' orders. Later, they defeated the spirit of Carthas himself, who revealed the source of his corruption and disappeared."}
