{"id": "3585", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3585", "title": "Eld Rune", "text": "An Eld rune is a low &lt;a href=\"Runes\"&gt;rune&lt;/a&gt; which can be &lt;a href=\"socket\"&gt;socket&lt;/a&gt;ed into equipment in \"\". Eld runes are the second most common runes in the game, but have a few high level uses, such as the &lt;a href=\"Silence%20Rune%20Word\"&gt;Silence rune word&lt;/a&gt;, and transmuting low quality weapons into normal weapons.\nEffects.\nSocketing an item with an Eld rune increases the item's level requirement to 11, unless it was already higher.\nSources.\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Countess\"&gt;The Countess&lt;/a&gt;'s extra rune drops on any difficulty can include Eld runes.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Hellforge\"&gt;Hellforge&lt;/a&gt; on normal difficulty has a 1 in 11 chance to drop an Eld rune as part of its quest reward.\nThe Act 2 Good treasure class has a chance to drop an Eld rune, as do higher Good treasure classes.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Horadric%20Cube\"&gt;Horadric Cube&lt;/a&gt; can transmute three &lt;a href=\"El%20Rune\"&gt;El runes&lt;/a&gt; into one Eld rune.\nRune Words.\nEld runes are used in these &lt;a href=\"Rune%20Words\"&gt;rune words&lt;/a&gt;:\nRecipes.\nEld runes are used in two &lt;a href=\"Horadric%20Cube\"&gt;Horadric Cube&lt;/a&gt; recipes."}
