{"id": "52127", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52127", "title": "Eldhaime Keep", "text": ",or simply Eldhaime (pronounced as eldhime), is a keep located in &lt;a href=\"Scosglen\"&gt;Scosglen&lt;/a&gt;, roughly to the northwest of &lt;a href=\"Kyovashad\"&gt;Kyovashad&lt;/a&gt;. \nLore.\nIt was was built by &lt;a href=\"Donan\"&gt;Donan&lt;/a&gt;, and serves as his home. As the home to one of the heroes of the &lt;a href=\"Days%20of%20Ash\"&gt;Days of Ash&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20Light\"&gt;Cathedral of Light&lt;/a&gt; set up a guard detail of &lt;a href=\"Knight%20Penitent\"&gt;Knight Penitent&lt;/a&gt;s at the keep. It has a barracks for the knights, and houses a number of servants and other workers. Underneath the great hall of the keep lies a well-hidden secret.\nHistory.\nAt the end of the Days of Ash, &lt;a href=\"Astaroth\"&gt;Astaroth&lt;/a&gt; was sealed in a soulstone by Donan, &lt;a href=\"Airidah\"&gt;Airidah&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Nafain\"&gt;Nafain&lt;/a&gt;. The three designed a ward that could contain the demon's presence. Donan and Nafain travelled \nto &lt;a href=\"Laglend%20Fern\"&gt;the edge&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Silvered%20Edgelands\"&gt;the wilderness&lt;/a&gt; near Kyovashad, where they sealed it within an underground cave. Donan later built Eldhaime over the the cave.\nIn-game.\n is a zone in &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;. It is visited as part of campaign."}
