{"id": "27175", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27175", "title": "Element of Celerity", "text": "Element of Celerity\u00a0was a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Crafting%20Material\"&gt;Legendary Crafting Material&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It requires a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Character%20Level\"&gt;Character Level&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0of 1 to use, is\u00a0&lt;a href=\"account%20bound\"&gt;account bound&lt;/a&gt;, and may be stacked up to 1000 times. It was required for the crafting of the &lt;a href=\"Fleeting%20Strap\"&gt;Fleeting Strap&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0legendary belt. As of patch 2.0.6., it no longer drops, and existing Elements may be sold for 50,000 Gold.\nIts icon was later reused for &lt;a href=\"Bottomless%20Potion%20of%20Chaos\"&gt;Bottomless Potion of Chaos&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe item had a chance to drop off the unique &lt;a href=\"Scavenger%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Scavengers&lt;/a&gt;:\n\"Found on those creatures that embody speed, combined with a strong desire to scavenge.\""}
