{"id": "8028", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8028", "title": "Elixir of Dexterity", "text": "The Elixirs of Dexterity are a type of &lt;a href=\"elixir\"&gt;elixir&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Game%29\"&gt;Diablo I&lt;/a&gt;\". They increase &lt;a href=\"Dexterity\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; by 1. They provide no bonus other than that to the stat they boost.\nThey can be purchased from &lt;a href=\"Pepin\"&gt;Pepin&lt;/a&gt;, only in single player, after a character ventures down to Hell (dungeon ) or enters the Hive or Crypt. Pepin will not offer elixirs that boost a stat that you've already maxed out. Elixirs of Dexterity can also be bought from &lt;a href=\"Adria\"&gt;Adria&lt;/a&gt; in single and multiplayer, but they appear on her items list randomly and infrequently. She only offers elixirs to players who have reached level 26 in multiplayer, or who have entered hell, the Hive, or the Crypt (in that game) in single player. Elixirs can be bought at a cost of 5000 &lt;a href=\"gold\"&gt;gold&lt;/a&gt;. They can also be dropped by &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s and , in the lower levels of the dungeons."}
