{"id": "32916", "revid": "180379", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=32916", "title": "Primeval Hunter", "text": "The Primeval Hunter is a type of &lt;a href=\"Animals\"&gt;beast&lt;/a&gt; enemy only encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Greyhollow%20Island\"&gt;Greyhollow Island&lt;/a&gt; zone of &lt;a href=\"Adventure%20Mode\"&gt;Adventure Mode&lt;/a&gt; in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIn-game.\nPrimeval Hunters appear like oversized red wolves with enormous fangs, and do not have any special abilities. They may spawn in packs from 1-3 to 10+, not mentioning support of other monsters. They run very quickly, and may efficiently block path.\nVisually, they look exactly like &lt;a href=\"Companion\"&gt;Companion&lt;/a&gt; wolves, except for color.\n&lt;a href=\"Aletur\"&gt;Aletur&lt;/a&gt; has a pack of dozen or so war wolves of unique blood and white color.\nDevelopment.\nPrimeval Hunter was designed to be a more natural enemy than some of the other island's more supernatural monsters."}
