{"id": "4524", "revid": "1687225", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4524", "title": "Principle Rune Word", "text": "Principle is the &lt;a href=\"Rune%20Word\"&gt;rune word&lt;/a&gt; \" for &lt;a href=\"Body%20Armor\"&gt;body armor&lt;/a&gt; in \"\".\nPrinciple is intended for the &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt; class. This rune word may be less difficult to construct than or , but a &lt;a href=\"Gul%20Rune\"&gt;Gul Rune&lt;/a&gt; is still quite a rare find. Still, the +2 to Paladin skills and life bonus would come in quite handy for any Paladin who has to get close to his foes.\nPrinciple was massively improved in \"\" thanks to the buffs &lt;a href=\"Holy%20Bolt\"&gt;Holy Bolt&lt;/a&gt; received: namely, the fact that it can now deal damage to demons as well as the undead, as well as its 100% chance to pierce. \nResult:"}
{"id": "51862", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51862", "title": "Prior Niv", "text": "Prior Niv was a resident of &lt;a href=\"Miettevin\"&gt;Miettevin&lt;/a&gt;. She made it her goal to be a nuisance to the &lt;a href=\"Zakarum\"&gt;Zakarum&lt;/a&gt; cloister in her hometown.\nBiography.\nThe Mountebank gathered hundreds of written indulgences from the cloister of Miettevin by posing as a priest. She scattered them in the street, spurring anger against the faith's profiteers. Later she infiltrated the church's reliquary to steal the jawbone of &lt;a href=\"Saint%20Alavaine\"&gt;Saint Alavaine&lt;/a&gt;. She did this by having herself delivered to the church's cellar in a wine barrel. She poured the barrel into the reliquary as she ran, and left red bootprints in the nave.\nThis earned her the enmity of the local church, and the temple knights chased her to &lt;a href=\"Fogswell\"&gt;Fogswell&lt;/a&gt;, where they flanked her on both banks of the river. She dove into the water as they loosed their arrows, and a stray broadhead cored her through the hand. She also gained a nemesis in the form of the paladin &lt;a href=\"Gurdannel\"&gt;Gurdannel&lt;/a&gt;. He challenged her to a duel, and she accepted for it to be held at the &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Foot%20of%20the%20Uxbers\"&gt;Frozen Foot of the Uxbers&lt;/a&gt;. She delayed her arrival twice, and snow stranded Gurdannel's entourage, ruining his reputation.\nThe Mountebank later set the church's cloister on fire, using only a pitch and cotton-wrapped pipe. As she watched from the hills, Gurdannel caught her and ran her through, though she leapt to her &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt; with a smile. She fell to earth near the town square. Stolen indulgences fluttered about her like feathers. Once townsfolk recognized her &lt;a href=\"corpse\"&gt;body&lt;/a&gt;, they killed Gurdannel.\nLegacy.\nPrior Niv's death sparked a violent upheaval and revolution that led to the exile of the faith from Miettevin. A statue was built in her honor in the square where she died.\nIn-game.\nPrior Niv is referenced in the item-text of \"&lt;a href=\"Untouchable%20Mountebank\"&gt;Untouchable Mountebank&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"item%20set\"&gt;item set&lt;/a&gt;."}
