{"id": "33590", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=33590", "title": "Prisoners of Kamyr", "text": "Prisoners of Kamyr is an\u00a0&lt;a href=\"event%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;event&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in &lt;a href=\"Act%20II%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act II&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It takes place in an event-specific area in the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Dahlgur%20Oasis\"&gt;Dahlgur Oasis&lt;/a&gt;, where a &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt; is sometimes offered to complete it.\nThe location comprises a T-shaped path including a short wood walkway, a slight cliff, and four Captive Guards. The area swarms with\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Fallen%20One%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Fallen Peons&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0and &lt;a href=\"Fallen%20Overseer\"&gt;Fallen Masters&lt;/a&gt;, and\u00a0includes a &lt;a href=\"Fallen%20Shaman%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Fallen Conjurer&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0or two.\nThe event doesn't officially start until the player frees one of the Captive Guards, so one can clear the area before freeing the Guards. Freed guards either thank the hero or say they must flee, then will run away in either case. After freeing all four, a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Unique%20monster\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; Fallen Overseer,\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Bramok%20the%20Overlord\"&gt;Bramok the Overlord&lt;/a&gt;, will spawn at the foot of the wooden walkway. Defeating it will complete the event and rewards gold, experience, and the challenge \"Prisoners of Kamyr\".\nFreeing a guard does not require channeling, but does occupy the character for a second or two and is uninterruptible. The guard in the southeast is tied up next to one of the volatile plant of the Oasis - it is wise to explode it before untying the guard."}
{"id": "50276", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50276", "title": "Prisoners of the Cult", "text": "Prisoners of the Cult is an &lt;a href=\"Bounty\"&gt;exploration bounty&lt;/a&gt; sometimes offered in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It is completed in &lt;a href=\"Stinging%20Winds\"&gt;Stinging Winds&lt;/a&gt;, where &lt;a href=\"The%20Nephalem\"&gt;The Nephalem&lt;/a&gt; must rescue five &lt;a href=\"Caldeum\"&gt;Caldeum&lt;/a&gt; Villagers from Iron Cages scattered throughout the zone, guarded by various members of the &lt;a href=\"Triune\"&gt;Triune&lt;/a&gt; cult. Opening a cage requires channeling uninterrupted for a short period. Freed villagers immediately leave via town portals. Freeing the last villager rewards gold and experience.\nAll of the Iron Cages are in the eastern part of the Stinging Winds, south of the &lt;a href=\"Khasim%20Outpost\"&gt;Khasim Outpost&lt;/a&gt; and north of the &lt;a href=\"Road%20to%20Alcarnus\"&gt;Road to Alcarnus&lt;/a&gt;. Unlike most other exploration bounties, the area is quite small, so not much exploration is required to find them all. While the Iron Cage objectives are only marked on the map once the hero is a medium distance away, as with other bounties of this type, this is rarely an impediment given the size of the area.\nThe &lt;a href=\"waypoint\"&gt;waypoint&lt;/a&gt; for the Stinging Winds is on the north side of the Khasim Outpost, opposite the bounty area, so some players may prefer to take the Road to Alcarnus waypoint instead, and head north to reach the cages. However, the difference is not great."}
