{"id": "43829", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43829", "title": "Purge the Depths", "text": " is a game mode in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nThe mode becomes accessible after the player's &lt;a href=\"warband\"&gt;warband&lt;/a&gt; has cleansed &lt;a href=\"Castle%20Cyrangar\"&gt;Castle Cyrangar&lt;/a&gt; for the first time. It takes place in the &lt;a href=\"Cyrangar%20Depths\"&gt;depths of the castle&lt;/a&gt; in a randomized dungeon. Notably, &lt;a href=\"ancestral%20weapons\"&gt;ancestral weapons&lt;/a&gt; have the highest drop rates in this mode, matched only by &lt;a href=\"Defense%20of%20Cyrangar\"&gt;Defense of Cyrangar&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis event is also the source of &lt;a href=\"Remnant\"&gt;Remnant&lt;/a&gt;s. After finishing a run, the Remnants collected are grouped into a Remnant Set and added to the Remnant Sets of your warband. Once created, remnant sets cannot be modified, and the only possible operations on them are equipping, locking/unlocking and deleting them.\nHistory.\nOriginally only raids composed of the members of the same warband could enter Purge the Depths. After the September 21 2023 update, this requirement was dropped and the event can be accessed from the NPC in Westmarch."}
